title: poppy seed cake
directions: Heat butter and juice in a saucepan.
Add enough sugar to make a glaze.
Pour over the cooled cake.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and drain excess fat. Stir in chili powder, oregano, sugar, salt and garlic salt.
Blend in tomato juice, onion, tomato paste and water. Bring to a boil. Add spaghetti and stir well. Cover and simmer, stirring frequently, for 30 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Mix ingredients until smooth, then roll into balls.
In double boiler, melt 3/4 wax paraffin and 3 (6 ounce) bags of chocolate chips.
Once melted, dip peanut butter balls in chocolate and place on wax paper to cool.
Best when refrigerated overnight.
Makes 100 to 120.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then gradually add scalding milk and vanilla.
Pour in pastry-lined pie pan and bake until a silver knife comes out clean.
The center may still be soft, but will set later.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(May bake at 350° for entire time.)

title: chicken quiche
directions: Rinse
broccoli
until thawed, drain.
Mix
broccoli,
2 cups cheese, chicken and
onion in 9-inch pie plate only.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt
and
pepper in blender until smooth (15 seconds on high),
pour
into
plate.
Bake
at
400° until knife inserted in center comes
out dry, 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remainder of cheese.
Bake	until cheese is melted, 1 or 2 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pound cake
directions: First, put in sour cream, then butter.
Add sugar; mix together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour a little bit at a time.
Put in flavoring.
Bake at 325°.

title: pralines
directions: Preheat oven to 350° line roasting pan with foil. Place one layer of graham crackers in pan. Combine other ingredients, bring to a boil, cook for 2 minutes. Pour over crackers. Bake 7 minutes. When cooled, break apart.

title: bacon cauliflower salad
directions: Layer the lettuce, cauliflower and bacon in bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and onions.
Drop by spoonfuls on lettuce mixture.
Sprinkle with dill weed and seasonings.
Cover and refrigerate. Toss before serving.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Refrigerate after it cools.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Place chicken on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or celery soup

title: creamy slaw
directions: Combine whipping cream, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper in a separate bowl.
Whip together with a wire whip.
Pour over cabbage; toss to coat well.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Add mincemeat and nuts.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine the first four ingredients and cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly. Allow to cool. Place strawberries in pie crust and
pour mixture over berries. Chill and top with whipped cream.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown sugar in an iron skillet.
Mix other ingredients in a saucepan at the same time.
Bring to boiling, stirring constantly. Try to have brown sugar and other mixture about the same temperature when putting together.
Mix together and pour into baked crust.
Make meringue or use Cool Whip for topping.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add a little milk and mix to a paste.
Add rest of milk and egg yolks.
Cook in double boiler until mixture thickens.
Pour into two baked pie shells.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: eva's apple pie
directions: Place apples and crushed pineapple with juice in a baking pan. Sprinkle sugar over fruit.
Sprinkle sugar mixed with cinnamon (if desired) over fruit.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of fruit.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in order, except nuts and egg whites. Beat well.
Add nuts and fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into an ungreased tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Let cool in pan.
Turn onto platter.

title: colorful cornbread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spoon into lightly greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting. Yield: Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, cinnamon and soda.
Beat eggs, sugar and oil with mixer.
Add dry ingredients and beat well. Fold in carrots and pecans. Pour into 3 x 8-inch well-greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: friendship brownie mix
directions: Layer the ingredients in the order given onto a wide-mouth 1-quart canning jar. Pack each layer in place before adding the next ingredient.

title: meat lovers olive pimiento loaf
directions: Crumble beef and pork into a large mixing bowl. Add onion, pepper and garlic; mix well. Add remaining ingredients as given and blend. Divide

mixture in half. Place each half in a 9 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake in a 375° oven for 35 to 45 minutes or until brown. Test for doneness in center. Cool in pan. Store airtight, chilled. Makes 2 loaves.

title: pork chop-n-potato bake
directions: Brown chops and sprinkle with salt.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, pepper and salt.
Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onion rings.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Arrange pork chops over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Top with remaining cheese and onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes longer.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add soups and peas.
Layer Tater Tots on bottom of casserole, then meat.
Top with Tater Tots.
Makes enough for 1 large or 2 small casseroles.
Freezes well.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: household hints
directions: Put in gallon jug and fill with water.
Fill spray bottles and use as needed.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Grease 9x13 inch pan.
Put coconut and nuts in pan.
Mix cake by directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix sugar, margarine and cream cheese together and spoon over cake.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: famous take-it-on-the trail mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in loosely covered container.
Makes 8 1/2 cups.

title: chopped liver
directions: Grind liver, eggs and onion.
Mix in seasonings.
Add drippings from pan to moisten.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Blend dry ingredients.
Cream butter, oil and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients; beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts. Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: pineapple scallop
directions: Mix well the first five ingredients.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Melt margarine.
Dice bread into small cubes and mix with margarine; when well mixed, cover top of pineapple mixture. Bake at 400° until thoroughly heated and brown on top.
Goes well with hot or cold ham.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix pie filling and 1 container Cool Whip together.
Blend well.
Put in baked pie shell.
Cover with remaining Cool Whip. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top, if desired.

title: pina colada wedges
directions: Beat cream cheese with sugar and rum until smooth.
Fold in 2 cups of Cool Whip, pineapple with juice and 2 cups of coconut.

title: grandma's potato salad
directions: Mix well in large bowl.
Cut potatoes into 1-inch squares.

title: light cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter at high speed with an electric mixer until soft and creamy.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating at low speed just until mixture is light.
Gently stir in vanilla and pecans. Chill until ready to spread.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased pan and bake 1 hour at 350° until golden brown.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Add jello to boiling water; stir to dissolve and add berries and salt.
Break angel food into pieces; put Cool Whip, jello mixture and berries over cake pieces.
Mix and chill.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine peanut butter and cream cheese. Add milk and confectioners sugar. Blend in whipped topping. Pour into crusts and freeze. Cut and serve when frozen.

title: overnight chicken casserole(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Mix all together, including uncooked macaroni and refrigerate overnight or longer in 1 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Add a package of frozen peas, if desired.

title: sin pie
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix butter, sugar, flour and milk in baking dish. Add baking powder and salt.
Pour into the baking dish over 1 quart of fruit mixed with 1 cup sugar.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Melt oleo in saucepan.
Add sugar.
Beat egg in milk and add to margarine. Bring to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Add nuts, coconut and cracker crumbs.
Pour over crackers in pan and put layer of whole crackers on top.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, syrup, salt, pie mix, vanilla, and butter. Spread nuts on bottom of crust, then the coconut.
Pour filling on top and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.. Nuts and coconut will rise to the top to form a crust.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan.
Cover and simmer until mixture cooks down.

title: bonbons
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, coconut and milk; shape into bite size balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together in top of double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture and let cool.

title: caramel kraut cake
directions: Stir together dry ingredients; reserve. Cream together butter and sugar. Add eggs to creamed mixture, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour. Add vanilla. Stir in sauerkraut and nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. Cool. Frost with Whipped Caramel Frosting.

title: porcupines (kalushka)(a german dish)
directions: Set up water and sauerkraut.
Meanwhile, mix ground meat, rice and seasonings.
Form into walnut size balls and place into boiling water and sauerkraut.
Bring to a boil again and simmer on low about 1 hour, covered. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Stir together first 5 ingredients.
Will not be smooth.
Put stick of butter on top and microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Stir with wooden spoon and add pecans.
Beat until loses some of its gloss.
Pour in buttered pan and refrigerate to harden.

title: blueberry crisp
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until bubbly.
Pour into a 9 x 14-inch pan and cover with Crumble Topping.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Pound
flour
into
beef.
Cut into 2-inch squares long and 1/2-inch
wide.
Melt
butter, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper in skillet.
Add beef and brown slowly.
Add water, sliced onions
and mushrooms.
Cook until beef is tender.
Add sour cream before serving while warm.
Serve on rice, bread or rolls.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat until hot 1 1/2 cups applesauce (unsweetened).
Add and mix 2 teaspoons of baking soda.
Add this mixture to the other ingredients.
Batter should be very thick.
Use rest of the flour as needed.
Grease pans with butter.
Loaf pan, 45 minutes at 350°. 8x12-inch pan, 30 minutes at 350°, or bake in coffee cans lined with waxed paper for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
These make nice gifts!

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden and bubbly.
tags: cream of chicken and mushroom soup

title: whipped cream biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Now whip the heavy cream and add.
Turn out on wax paper and knead lightly.
Pat out 3/4 inch thick.
Cut and place on a slightly greased cookie sheet. Bake for 12 minutes at 450°.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook lasagna.
Drain the lasagna and run cold water and drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: ritz chicken
directions: Boil 1	chicken;
pick	off
bones and cut in bite size bits. Mix together cut up chicken, melted butter, sour cream, chicken soup,
salt
and pepper to taste.
Crush about 40 Ritz crackers and line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spoon in chicken mixture and sprinkle another 40 crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: beef roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast lightly.
Sprinkle sauce on roast, then onion soup mix.
Put 1 can mushroom soup (undiluted) on top of that.
Place on large sheet of aluminum foil.
Fold over and seal. Cook in 300° oven for about 3 hours.
Be sure to put in a pan in case the foil breaks.

title: pastry
directions: Take 1/3 cup flour and salt mixture and mix water with it to form a paste.
Cut Crisco (12 tablespoons) in remaining flour. Add flour-paste and blend thoroughly.
Divide and roll out.

title: champagne punch
directions: Slice fruit with rinds on.
Combine fruits with other ingredients, except champagne, and let stand overnight.
When you are ready to serve the punch, put a large block of ice in your punch bowl and pour the mixture over it.
Add the champagne.

title: tangy cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce until blended.
Refrigerate until gelatin mixture is consistency of egg whites.
Beat on high speed of mixer until foamy.
Fold in yogurt, celery, nuts and apples.
Pour into 6-cup mold. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
To serve, unmold onto serving plate.
Garnish with additional yogurt or whipped cream and celery leaves.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: recipe for a good cook
directions: Blend well and place in a sunny, cheery kitchen.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Set aside 1 cup of dry cake mix.
Beat 1 egg.
Add 1/2 cup melted butter.
Mix into rest of dry cake mix.
Press into bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
In another bowl, beat 3 eggs.
Add milk, 3/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and pumpkin pie filling.
Mix together and pour over cake.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 2 tablespoons melted butter and nuts with 1 cup of dry cake mix.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes.
Insert knife to test doneness.

title: sweetbreads
directions: Soak the sweetbreads in cold water for 30 minutes.
After removing

title: co co not cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and coconut extract.
Add egg and beat.
Stir in Bix-Mix and spud flakes.
Cover bowl and chill for about 1 hour.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Mix together well the sugar, shortening, eggs, vanilla and almond.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt. Mix flour and milk with shortening ingredients well.
Chill overnight.
Then roll on well floured board.
Cut in shapes. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Cut kielbasa into 1 or 2-inch pieces.
Fry or broil and drain off fat.
Cook cabbage in small amount of water or in microwave.

title: dumplings for stew
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Work in butter with tips of fingers or cut in with 2 knives.
Add milk gradually.
Use more if necessary to make a soft dough.
Round bits of dough up on teaspoon and push on top of stew.
Quickly adjust cover and steam for about 12 minutes.
Do not open until the time is out or the dumplings will not be light.

title: salsa
directions: First, peel tomatoes as follows:
Put in boiling water for 2 minutes, then grab each with tongs and dunk into cold water.
Skin easily peels off.
Chop tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients in saucepan and heat to a boil.

title: baked ham concord
directions: Cover ham with water and add cloves, cinnamon, onions and allspice.
Simmer slowly for 20 minutes per pound of ham.
Remove any skin and cut fat in a crisscross design.
Put ham in roasting pan and cover with mixture of bread crumbs and brown sugar.
Bake 5 minutes in a 450° oven.
Reduce heat to 300° and baste with grape juice every few minutes.
Bake 18 minutes per pound at 300°.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine uncooked rice, water, undrained corn, carrot and thyme; bring to a boil, then stir in soup.
Pour mixture into a rectangular baking dish.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: barbecue elk ribs
directions: Roll ribs in flour and brown in hot oil.
Then put half of ribs in crock-pot and add half of barbecue sauce.
Put in the rest of the ribs and cover with remaining barbecue sauce.
Cover and cook for approximately 8 hours.

title: strawberry angel food
directions: Mix jello in 2 cups of water and put in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Mix pudding according to directions on package.
Put strawberries aside to thaw or you may use fresh ones (add sugar to taste in fresh ones).
Put Cool Whip in refrigerator overnight to soften (night before).

title: golfers special pot roast
directions: Place meat on heavy-duty foil.
Cover with onion soup mix and mushroom soup.
Surround with fresh vegetables.
Seal tightly, leaving about 6 inches above the meat.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Put all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Mix well with fork.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Do not frost.
Good for picnics or camping.

title: fiesta pork kabobs
directions: Cook corn in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain.
On 4 long skewers, alternately thread meat, sweet pepper and corn.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Wrap each apple slice in a crescent roll and place in baking dish. Heat oleo, sugar and cinnamon until sugar is dissolved; pour over apple dumplings. Then pour can of Mountain Dew over all and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vinaigrette francaise(dressing for vegetables)
directions: Combine all with any combination of fresh vegetables.

title: rich lemon bars(makes 24 to 36 bars)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly. Press onto bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: "mom's" apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, heat sugar and water until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves the side of bowl. Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead just until smooth. Roll dough out into a large rectangle about 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle cinnamon over apples, then sprinkle apples over the dough.

title: zucchini fudge cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in vanilla. Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add to the creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk. Stir in zucchini. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round baking pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Yield: 12 to 14 servings.

title: sugar puffs
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, nutmeg, milk and egg together.
Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Roll into cinnamon sugar.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine in bowl with half the butter, salt, pepper, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Blend together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the remaining butter and corn flakes (or chips) and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss.
If desired, mound salad in lettuce cups and garnish with maraschino cherries.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: macaroni with hamburger balls
directions: Mix onions, salt, pepper and hamburger meat. Form into small balls and fry until golden brown. Cook macaroni in saltwater until tender. Drain. Add tomato juice and meat balls to macaroni. Simmer together for 10 minutes. Serve.

title: creole fish
directions: Pour 2 tablespoons margarine in bottom of baking pan.
Combine celery, carrots, olives, green pepper, onions, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Spread half of mixture in bottom of pan.
Place fish on top.
Cover with remaining mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.
Calories:

title: baked squash
directions: Wash squash and cut into pieces.
Add squash to a small amount of boiling salted water.
Cover.
When water returns to boiling, lower heat and cook until tender.
Drain thoroughly and mash.
Add other ingredients to squash and mix well.
Pour into a 1-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: upside down apple gingerbread cake
directions: Pour 1/4 cup butter into 9-inch square pan.
Arrange apples over butter.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup brown sugar.
Set aside.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Stir to blend well.
Cover bowl and chill one hour or overnight.
Serve with uncooked cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, celery, cucumbers, etc.

title: quick cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in 1 cup cold water until tender.
Add sugar and cook about 5 minutes.
Soften gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water. Add to hot cranberries and stir until gelatine is dissolved.
Cool until it begins to thicken.
Add celery, nuts and salt.
Stir. Refrigerate.

title: guatemalan chirmol salsa(chirmol)
directions: Grill green onions and chop. Grill tomatoes until soft, grill corn. Combine tomatoes, onions, and garlic in a bowl and puree. Add olive oil, lime juice, grilled corn kernels, cilantro, jalapeno, and salt and pepper (to taste). Serve hot or chilled with tortilla chips or on any dish.

title: easy apple pie
directions: Spray 9-inch pie plate with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs, reserving 1 tablespoon for garnish; set aside.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add sherbet and all fruit, fold in whipped cream and chill until firm.

title: pigs in blanket
directions: Take the leaves off of cabbage.
Put in pan of water; cook for 20 minutes, then take leaves of cabbage and cool them.

Mix hamburger, the rice and onion together, then put 2 tablespoons of the hamburger, rice and onion together on each leaf of cabbage and roll each one up with the rice, hamburger and onion in a big bread pan.
Pour tomato sauce and water over pigs in blanket in pan.
Put in oven.
Bake about 2 1/2 hours.

title: rhubarb strawberry rolls
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder, and 1 Tbsp. sugar;
cut in shortening until mixture is like coarse crumbs.
Add combined egg and milk, stirring just until moistened.
Set aside, make syrup of water and 3/4 cup sugar;
cook 5 minutes.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Mix rhubarb and strawberries.
Roll out dough on slighlty floured surface 1/2 inch thick; brush with melted butter; spread with fruit mixture;
roll as for jelly roll.
Cut 1/2-inch slices; place, cut side down, in hot syrup.
Bake in oven (425°) for 30 minutes.

title: key lime pie(blue ribbon winner, georgia state fair)
directions: Prepare pie shell; cool.
Beat egg yolks until thick and bubbly.
Beat in the condensed milk, lime juice and sugar.
Turn the filling into pie shell.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: curry dip
directions: Makes 1 cup dip.
Mix all ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Must use Hellmann's mayonnaise.

title: cajun party mix
directions: In a 4-quart bowl or 13 x 9 x 2-inch microwave save dish, melt margarine on High for 1 minute.
Stir in parsley, celery salt, garlic powder, cayenne pepper and pepper sauce.
Mix well. Gradually add cereals, stirring until all spices are evenly coated.
Cook on High 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 minutes, stirring every 1 1/2 minutes.
Add onions.
Mix well.
Cook an additional 1 1/2 minutes.
Spread on paper towel to cool.

title: scrimshaw inn rum pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups milk, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
In medium bowl, beat together remaining milk, flour, cornstarch and egg yolks. Add hot mixture in a thin stream, whisking constantly to prevent eggs from curdling.
Return mix to saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring until thick.
Cool slightly.
Beat in vanilla, butter and rum.
Pour into pie shell and chill.
Top with whipped cream and grated chocolate before serving.

title: kid's crunchies
directions: Microwave chocolate chips on High for 4 minutes.
Stir in peanut butter and mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper and refrigerate until firm. Makes approximately 36.
Kids love them!

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Slightly flatten each chicken breast.
Place in baking dish. Cover with foil and bake in preheated 425° oven for 20 minutes. Remove foil and drain.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, oregano and pepper sauce.
Stir to dissolve cornstarch.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken and top with cheese.
Return to oven and bake 5 minutes, uncovered, or until heated through.
Garnish with chopped parsley and serve with hot, cooked rice, if desired.

title: banana carrot bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 5 x 9-inch loaf pan, greased lightly, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix dressing mix with milk and mayonnaise.
Soften cheeses and add Ranch mix.
Put bacon bits on waxed paper.
Roll cheese ball on bacon bits.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pam's creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a medium bowl, beat egg yolks with Eagle Brand milk, lemon juice and food coloring.
Pour into prepared pastry shell and bake for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Chill. Spread with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: koch kaese(cooked cheese)
directions: Add the soda to the cheese and stir.
Add the flour, mix and let stand about an hour.
A warm place helps the fermentation. Melt the oleo in a heavy saucepan and add the cheese mixture. Cook on low heat and stir until stringy and somewhat firm, like pudding.
Pour into serving dish or cartons.
Enjoy!

title: oaten honeycomb
directions: Bring milk to boil; sprinkle flakemeal in and cook slowly for about 15 minutes, stirring all the time.
Leave to cool, then beat in (one by one) ground almonds, honey, sugar, raisins or lemon peel, cinnamon, melted butter and beaten egg yolks.
Mix well and finally add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Put into a buttered bowl or basil; cover and steam over hot water for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn out and serve hot with warm melted honey or cream.
It is more delicate in flavor if made with lemon peel.

title: marty's dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. May be made a day ahead. May be frozen. Bring to room temperature before baking. Serve with crackers or Fritos chips.

title: sunday chicken casserole
directions: Pour water into baking pan (or dish).
Distribute rice over water.
Place chicken with fat side up on rice.
Sprinkle salt and pepper and dot with margarine.
Spread soup over chicken.
Slice onion on top.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: heath bar trifle
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Poke holes in cake.
When warm, pour Kahlua over cake; let cool.
Mix pudding according to package directions and set aside.
If you have a large trifle bowl, use 3 packages.
In a trifle bowl, use 1/2 of the amount for each layer. Layer 1:
1/2 crumbled cake.
Layer 2:
pieces of candy bar.
Layer 3:
1/2 of pudding.
Layer 4:
1/2 of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers again.
Top with candy bar shavings.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, then ice.

title: chocolate chip, date, nut cake
directions: Pour boiling water over dates.
Let stand until cool.
Add soda to dates and water.
Cream together shortening and sugar. Add eggs to sugar and shortening and beat.
Add alternately with date mixture the cocoa, salt and flour.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and chopped nuts over top. Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Mix margarine, sugar and eggs together.
Add flour mixture, a little at a time.
Add chocolate syrup and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients together.
Mix all together in a 5-quart Dutch oven and simmer for 1 hour.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef until tender.
In a separate pot, cook potatoes until tender.
Use a large soup pot and add beef and its juices. Then drain the potatoes and add to the beef.
Drain all the liquid from the vegetables and add to the beef.
After all ingredients are added, add water until soup is covered (about 1-inch over the mixture).
Bring to a boil, then turn to low heat.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours, stirring frequently.

title: pasta salad
directions: Chop the first 6 ingredients.
Cook linguine; drain in colander with cold water until cool.
In a large bowl, add linguine, chopped vegetables, crab meat and baby shrimp; mix.
Add Italian dressings and salad seasoning; mix well and chill.

title: st. paddy's dream dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
You can use the red cherries, if you like.
I also use the colored marshmallows to give the dessert a tantalizing color.

title: maple mustard glazed spareribs
directions: Sprinkle spareribs with the 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Tie pickling spice in several thicknesses of cheesecloth to make a bouquet garni; set aside.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Combine seasoning mix and beans in a small bowl. Spread beans in an 8-inch square baking dish. Top with sour cream, guacamole, cheese, salsa, chillies and green onions. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice and stir in thoroughly.
Add oil, slowly beating constantly, and continue to beat until thick.
Add poppy seeds and beat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Store in refrigerator. Serve over fruit salad. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle 6 ounces chocolate chips on top.
Add nuts if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pizza bubble bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths.
Coat in pizza sauce.
Place touching in greased pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: banana cream pie
directions: In heavy saucepan, dissolve cornstarch in water; stir in sweetened condensed milk and egg yolks.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Add margarine and vanilla; cook slightly.
Arrange 2 bananas on bottom of pastry. Pour filling over bananas; cover.
Chill 4 hours or until set. Spread top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with remaining banana slices.

title: sweetheart beet mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients; except sour cream.
Fold in sour cream. Pour into mold.
Chill.

title: shortcake(good with strawberries)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and milk; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix together like thick cake batter.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until done in center.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Turn on oven to 400°.
In large mixing bowl, put the blueberries.
Sift over them the dry ingredients; stir a little. Pour on milk, egg and oil; stir just until moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Divide into a dozen muffin cups, which have been either lined with paper cupcake cups or greased well.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Spray a 9-inch pan or oblong baking dish with Pam.
Spread apples in bottom of pan. Spread half of cinnamon and brown sugar over apples.
Combine sugar, flour and egg (it will be crumbly).
Spread over apples and cinnamon.
Spread remaining cinnamon and brown sugar over flour mixture.
Melt margarine and pour over whole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Clean and grind peppers, tomatoes and onions.
Sprinkle salt over mixture and let stand overnight.
Drain and add sugar, mustard seed, celery seed, turmeric and vinegar.
Cook slowly for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Beat in butter.
Add vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: stuffing for tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Refrigerate.
Use as a stuffing for cherry or regular tomatoes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage; remove from pan.
Using sausage fat, cook equal amounts of sliced onions and green pepper.
Cook until tender; drain.
Place all in casserole.
Pour jar of spaghetti sauce over all.
Top with Mozzarella cheese; heat until melted.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Combine corn, creamed corn and eggs.
Add mixture of sugar, cornstarch, seasoned salt, dry mustard and minced onions.
Stir in milk and melted butter.
Pour into greased 3-quart casserole. Bake at 400° for 1 hour, stirring once.

title: macaroni oceane
directions: Saute scallops, shrimp, crab meat and mushrooms in butter. Add onion, salt and pepper.
Add white wine and cook until liquid is reduced to one-half.
Add heavy cream.
Thicken to desired consistency by boiling down, stirring constantly.

title: crock-pot spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion and pepper.
Then put all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on medium all day.
You do not have to brown hamburger.

title: lemon bars
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry crunch salad
directions: Combine pretzel pieces, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Spread in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for seven (7) minutes.
Remove and allow to cool thoroughly.
Blend softened cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar thoroughly.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread evenly over first layer.
Dissolve gelatin in hot water; allow to cool to room temperature.
Add strawberries. Spoon evenly over cream cheese layer.
Chill until firm.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Brown diced onion.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add tomato paste, stewed tomatoes, bouillon cubes, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables; bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put all ingredients in a crock-pot on low until cheese has melted.
Stir as needed.

title: sour cream and cherry coffee cake
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add almond and eggs; mix. Add remaining ingredients alternately.
Top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in boiling salted water as directed on the package. Add remaining ingredients and pour into 3-quart casserole.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour.

title: applesauce doughnuts
directions: Combine and sift together the first 7 ingredients.
Beat together the shortening, sugar and eggs until thick and creamy. Beat in vanilla, applesauce and buttermilk.
Add flour mixture, 1 cup at a time, beating smooth after each addition.
Chill batter about 1 hour.
Turn out on lightly floured board and roll out 3/8-inch thick.
Cut into 2 1/2-inch doughnuts (leftover biscuits may be re-rolled once and cut).

title: fudge 1
directions: Melt chocolate morsels with milk (can be melted in microwave). Add other ingredients.
Spread in waxed paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: peachy angel food alaskan
directions: Cut cake horizontally into three parts.
Spread a layer of ice cream on top of each layer of cake.
Lay peaches on top of ice cream (single layer).
Spread whipped topping on each layer also. Stack cake back together.
Freeze for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fudge
directions: Stir the sugar, butter and milk together; cook for 5 minutes after it begins to boil.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered pan and cool.
Slice.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Put pudding in a bowl.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold in pineapple using the juice, too.
Add marshmallows.
Pour into a serving dish.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill overnight.

title: baked spinach-topped tomatoes
directions: Halve larger tomatoes.
Scoop out centers.
Place tomatoes in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Cook margarine and onion 5 minutes.
Add spinach, bread crumbs, egg, garlic powder and 1/4 cup cheese. Mound mixture into and onto tomatoes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Um, um good!

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and ReaLemon; mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until set.
Cool.
Chill thoroughly.
Spread sour cream on top.
Serve with topping if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: best sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring oil, vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Let cool.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss several times to mix.
Serves approximately 20.

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.

title: coconut and pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, brown sugar, eggs and water.
Beat until creamy. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats, morsels and extract. Drop by slightly rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: frozen lemon delight
directions: Heat margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs and sugar. Put half in bottom of 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Mix sweetened milk and lemonade by large spoon.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Sprinkle rest of crumb mixture on top.
Place in freezer. Cut into squares.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix zucchini and salt in a bowl; let stand 15 minutes.
Drain, squeezing liquid out.
Return zucchini to bowl.
Add eggs, flour, herb seasoning and 1/2 cup cheese.
Mix.
Spread mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until the center sets.
Meanwhile brown mushrooms in butter. After initial baking, spoon 1/2 of pizza sauce over the zucchini mixture.
Cover with mushrooms and 1/2 of olives.
Sprinkle with peppers and 1/2 of remaining cheese.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sandy's fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa in a medium pot to break up cocoa. Add evaporated milk.
Stir until dissolved.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Boil until soft ball stage (tested in a glass of water and can be easily rolled between fingers) about 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add butter and vanilla.
Beat; pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook until vegetables are tender, about 10 minutes.
I use a 6 1/2 x 8-inch baking dish, well-greased.
Alternate layers of squash and crumbs until all ingredients are used, finishing with crumbs on top.
Pour mushroom soup over.
Rinse can with 1/4 cup milk or water and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: jalapeno pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix eggs, cream, salt, pepper and nutmeg together.
Place peppers and bacon in the bottom of the pie crust. (Chorizo, ground pork, ham or other meat may be substituted for the bacon, if desired.)
Cover peppers and bacon with cheese, then pour egg mixture over all.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Cool for 30 minutes.

title: mrs. foxworth's bloody marys
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a 1-gallon jug.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: frosted zucchini cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg, vanilla and sour cream.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir into shortening mixture.
Stir in zucchini, raisins and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until lightly browned.
Remove to wire rack, then frost.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine the first 9 ingredients in a shallow 2-quart baking dish and mix well.
Remove 1/4 of this mixture and set aside.
Add shrimp to baking dish and coat thoroughly.
Combine bread crumbs with reserved butter sauce and sprinkle over the shrimp.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve immediately.
(Good with rice, broccoli and French bread to get all the juices.)

title: aunt violet's pickles
directions: Drain pickles.
Pour sugar over and add the remainder of the ingredients. Use a BIG bowl with a snap-on lid.
Stir well and shake often.
These are ready to eat in 24 hours.
DELICIOUS!

title: shake and bake chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in milk; drain.
Place margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt in 400° oven until melted.
Combine flour, salt, paprika and poultry seasoning in paper bag.
Shake well.
Place chicken in flour mixture.
Shake until well coated.
Place in melted butter.
Turn once to coat.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and pepper, if desired.
Bake uncovered in 400° oven for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes or until tender.

title: midge's chicken pie
directions: Warm Veg-All and all ingredients. Pour into pastry shell. Cover with pastry shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: strawberry pretzel congealed salad
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix pretzel crumbs, butter and 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Pat into a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake for 8 minutes, then cool.
Mix the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and Cool Whip; spread on pretzel layer.
Combine jello and boiling water. Stir in strawberries.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate until top is congealed and ready to serve.

title: chile con queso
directions: Heat tomatoes.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Slowly add cheeses until all is melted.
Serve warm as dip for tortilla chips.

title: pork chops alexander
directions: Pour boiling water over apricots; cool to room temperature. Drain, reserving liquid.
Trim fat from pork chops on both sides. Heat fat in skillet.
Brown chops on both sides in hot fat. Combine seasonings, syrup and reserved liquid; pour over chops. Place apricots on top of chops.
Cover; cook over low heat for 1 hour.
Add a little water, if necessary, to prevent sticking. Cook, uncovered, for last few minutes, spooning sauce over chops.

title: swedish meatballs with dill sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in butter until tender. Soak bread crumbs in milk 5 minutes.
Add eggs and spices; mix well.
Mix in meat and onions.
Shape into walnut sized balls and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: frozen salad
directions: Blend all ingredients except whipped cream.
Fold whipped cream into mixture.
Pour into mold and freeze for 6 hours.

title: dream pie
directions: Beat whipped topping with 1 cup milk and vanilla.
Beat high for 6 minutes or until peaks form.
Add remaining milk and pie filling mix; blend at low.
Beat on high for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into shells and chill.

title: peanut butter chocolate balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Roll into balls and chill.
Melt chocolate with paraffin.
Dip chilled balls in chocolate; chill. Store in refrigerator.

title: honey fried fish
directions: In a bowl, beat Egg and Honey.
In another bowl combine the next 5 ingredients.
Dip Fillets into Egg and Honey mixture then coat with Cracker mixture.
In a large skillet, heat Oil.
Fry Fillets over medium heat for 3 - 4 minutes or until Fillet flakes easily with fork.
Drizzle with Honey and Lemon if desired. Yields:
4 servings.

title: scallops with gorgonzola and cream
directions: In a large saucepan, saute the scallions and scallops over medium-high heat until scallops are lightly browned, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Add the wine and continue cooking until the wine has been reduced to a syrup.
Stir in the heavy cream and reduce by 1/3, then add the Gorgonzola and stir constantly until a creamy sauce consistency is achieved.
Serve immediately over linguini. Serves 4.

title: calzone
directions: In saucepan cook meat and onion until meat is brown; remove and drain off fat.
Stir in pizza sauce, olives, basil and oregano. Cut a thin slice from the top of each roll.
Hollow out the bottom of the roll to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Sprinkle about 3 tablespoons of cheese into bottom of each roll.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix together all ingredients except fruit. Put in a 9 X 13 baking dish. Cover with canned fruit. Bake until brown about 45 minutes at 350°. Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: red cabbage slaw
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
In large bowl, combine beets, cabbage and onion.
In saucepan, combine vinegar, sugar and reserved beet juice.
Bring to boiling point.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate 4 to 5 hours or overnight, tossing occasionally.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Season beef with salt and saut in heavy skillet.
Drain; set aside.
Combine cheese, corn meal, salt, onion and peppers in large bowl; mix well.
Stir eggs into milk.
Add to dry ingredients and stir just to moisten.
Spoon half of batter into greased 2-quart casserole.
Place beef over batter and top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together, except mayonnaise and mustard. Add the mayonnaise and mustard; mix well.
Garnish with avocado, tomatoes and lettuce, if desired.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Drain pineapple; save 3 tablespoons juice.
Combine flour and sugar; stir into reserved pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks.
Mix.
Pour mixture into 1-quart casserole dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Melt margarine and mix with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and serve.
It is delicious served with ham or pork.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place 6 to 8 skinned chicken breasts in a baking pan.
Pour dressing over chicken and bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with corn flake crumbs and 1/2 stick melted butter. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Prepare jumbo shells according to package directions; drain. In bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, egg, bread crumbs and Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon mixture into shells.
Place shells in 12 x 8-inch baking pan.
Pour sauce over shells.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pizzaburgers
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain.
Add tomato soup and stir.
Top with oregano and shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Serve on toasted hamburger rolls.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix pudding, milk, Amaretto and Cool Whip together.
Cut up the fruit.
Dip and eat.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle water with hand to make a medium soft dough.
Let rest 15 minutes.
Roll dough; cut. Fry in about 1/4 cup hot oil until golden.
Great with honey butter.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg and salt and form into small balls and broil until brown.
Cook the green pepper and onion in the butter until tender.
Stir in the remaining ingredients and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: canned tomato soup
directions: Cover celery with water and boil until tender.
Grind celery and onions and add to remaining ingredients.
Stir and heat.
Put in jar and process in boiling water bath for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat well; pour into freezer.
Add enough milk to fill line.

title: busy day chicken
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour rice in pan.
Place chicken breasts on top of rice.
In a bowl, mix together water, mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Pour liquid mixture over rice and chicken.
Cover with foil; bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: strawberry yogurt shake
directions: Combine pineapple juice, yogurt, strawberries and sugar in blender container.
Process until smooth.
Pour into glasses.

title: low-fat vegetable meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except catsup.
Coat loaf pan with cooking spray.
Shape meat mixture into loaf pan.
Spread catsup over meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.
Yields 6 servings, about 188 calories per serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Put 2 cups in 11-inch dish.
Refrigerate until it sets.
Spread sour cream over it and add remaining mixture. Refrigerate until time to serve.

title: mama's poor man's cornbread
directions: Heat oil in skillet to fry temperature.
Drop thick cornmeal batter by tablespoonful into hot oil and flatten to make individual cakes.
Cook until brown.
Turn and fry until brown on other side.
Do not fry too fast so bread will cook through.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Combine egg, sugar and oil.
Mix until light yellow.
Sift flour and cinnamon.
Stir into egg mixture (this will be stiff). Add vanilla, apples and walnuts.
Grease and flour 9-inch cake pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: canned beet pickle
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar, water and vinegar in an enameled pan.
Put cooked, sliced beets in the hot syrup.
Simmer together for 10 minutes until hot enough to can.

title: country sausage macaroni and cheese
directions: Crumble and cook sausage in medium skillet until browned. Drain on paper towels. Combine milk, Cheddar cheese and mustard in medium saucepan. Cook and stir over low heat until cheese melts and mixture is smooth. Stir in sausage, tomatoes, mushrooms, green onions and cayenne pepper. Remove from heat. Cook macaroni according to package directions. Drain. Combine hot macaroni and cheese mixture in large bowl. Toss until well coated. Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake 15 to 20 minutes. Stir. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes more. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Refrigerate leftovers. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine and pour into large unbaked pie shell.
You can leave out the coconut and use 1 cup of cooked, mashed and drained pumpkin.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until tested done.

title: garlicky mashed potatoes *
directions: In heavy saucepan, add potatoes, garlic and quartered onion to 1 inch cold water.
Cover tightly on high heat; when steam escapes, reduce to low.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Drain excess water.
Place back on heat to dry (30 seconds).
Mash until smooth.
Add butter.
Slowly beat in milk.
Season.
Add chives. Keep warm in 275° oven.
Serves 6.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cream of tartar and add to above.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal, Rice Krispies, coconut and chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool slightly before removing from pan.

title: texas trash
directions: Mix butter, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and Tabasco sauce.
Pour over mixture of remaining items.
Put in oven at 250°. Stir every 15 minutes for 1 hour.

title: chinese pork
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over pork.
Marinate 2 to 3 hours. Bake at 325° approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Baste seldom.

title: salsa
directions: *This makes a very, very hot sauce.
For milder sauce, use fewer jalapeno chiles and less juice.

title: tim's steamed cranberry pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Steam in a tightly covered 1 pound coffee can for 1 1/2 hours.
Slice and serve warm with sauce following.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Stir in chicken and spices.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Makes delicious tacos or enchiladas.
If you like a spicier sauce, substitute salsa for milk.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into greased loaf pan or 9 x 9-inch square pan; bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: glossy chocolate sour cream frosting
directions: Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler over hot, not boiling, water, stirring constantly until completely melted. Remove from heat; beat in sour cream, confectioners sugar and vanilla.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add bouillon and cool until slightly thickened.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and chill.

title: oriental fruit barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan and simmer 4 minutes.
Great on kabobs, pork ribs or whatever!

title: molded ham salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Bring tomato juice, vinegar, paprika, green onion and tabasco to boiling.
Add soaked gelatin to boiling mixture.
Allow to cool.
Mix ground ham with salad dressing and add to cooled gelatin mixture.
Pour into oiled ring mold.
To serve, unmold and fill center with celery leaves or cottage cheese.
Serves 4-6.
May be used as salad or spread for crackers.

title: pumpkin cream pie
directions: Mix
ingredients
and bake in 2 large pie shells for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Add all ingredients in order.
Mix and pour into large baking dish.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Put the peach pie filling in first; after each fruit stir the pie filling to cover the fresh fruit.
If desire, put Cool Whip on top.

title: fruit cake squares
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at at time, and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Mix in flour.
Set aside 1 cup of dough and spread remaining dough into a greased and floured 9 x 13 inch pan. Spread pie filling on top.
Drop remaining dough on top of pie filling.
After dropping remaining dough on top of filling take a knife and spread the dough so the globs of dough connect slightly with one another.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: "gook"
directions: Sprinkle dry Jell-O in cottage cheese, stir in good, mix well. Add fruit (drained, if using canned).
Stir in Cool Whip.

title: iced coffee
directions: Heat coffee and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Let cool.
Add all other ingredients.
Put in plastic bags and freeze.
Take out 2 hours before serving.
Serves 18 cups.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a large bowl; add sugar, shortening, salt and eggs.
Add flour, one cup at a time.
Leave in bowl and put in refrigerator overnight.
Take out what you need.
Roll and cut.
Brush with melted butter.
Let stand 2 hours.
Brush with butter.

title: swedish kringle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like pie crust.
Pat into 2 strips 3 inches wide and the length of a cookie sheet.
In pan, bring to a boil, the next two ingredients.
Add 1 cup flour and 3 eggs one at a time, beating well and add 1 teaspoon almond extract.
Spread this on top of the two pie crust strips and bake 55 minutes at 350°.
When cool, frost with 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar, 1/4 cup margarine, 1 teaspoon almond extract and about 2 tablespoons milk. The only sugar is in the frosting.

title: pepper jelly mold
directions: Blend the cream cheese until smooth.
Add jelly; mix.
Soften gelatine in cold milk, then add boiling milk to dissolve gelatine. Combine gelatine mixture to cream cheese mixture.
Pour into a 3 1/2-cup mold.
Chill until set.
Unmold onto a serving plate. Garnish with a bow made of pimento to look like a Christmas wreath.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour into a baking dish.
Cook at 325° until firm, 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: italian tomatoes
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, salt, pepper, oregano and sugar.
Pour over tomatoes and peppers.
Let set to marinate 1/2 hour to 3 hours.
Serve chilled.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.
Can be served over spaghetti noodles.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Put sausage links into each triangle.
Roll up.
Place on baking sheet, seam down, on rack.
Bake according to package directions.

title: chicken nicoise
directions: Brown chicken parts in olive oil and butter.
Remove to a baking dish with fat and bake at 375° for about 15 minutes, basting once.

title: baked beans
directions: Chop onion and brown in frying pan.
Add 5 tablespoons mustard and mix well.
Add hamburger, chop and cook until brown.
Add tomato catsup, then add pork and beans.
Mix thoroughly.
Put in baking dish.
Crisscross bacon.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and bake for 35 minutes at about 375°.
Dip off grease when done, while beans are hot.

title: fr. paul's lasagna
directions: Mix ingredients in a tall pot.
Cook over medium heat; stir frequently.
Do not cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: jewish style cake
directions: Mix 3/4 cup sugar with cinnamon; set aside.
Into mixing bowl, sift together 2 cups sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well in the center.
Add orange juice, oil and eggs; beat well.
Pour one-third of batter into a well creamed cake pan.
Slice one-half of apples over batter; sprinkle with one-half of the cinnamon. Pour in another one-third of the batter; slice the rest of the apples over it.
Sprinkle in the rest of the cinnamon.
Add the rest of the batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours (until cake tests done).
This is a heavy cake.

title: apple dip ii
directions: Mix cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until fluffy using an electric mixer. Spread about 1/2-inch thick onto a platter. Heat the Marzetti's caramel apple dip in the microwave for 1 minute; it must be warm to spread evenly. Next, spread caramel on top of cream cheese mixture on platter. Garnish with chopped nuts. Serve with apple wedges, celery or pretzels. Serves 8 to 10.

title: sandwich buns
directions: Thaw bread as directed.
Cut loaf into 8 equal pieces.
Place on a greased 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Let raise to desired height.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.

title: play dough with kool-aid
directions: Mix together water and Kool-Aid, then mix all ingredients together in a saucepan in order listed.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture gathers together.

title: basic omelette
directions: Beat eggs well; add water.
Pour in hot iron skillet with butter.
Let edges brown, fold over and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread.
Add corn, onions and jalapenos; set aside. Brown hamburger; add 3/4 of cheese.
Mix together with cornbread mixture.
Pour into greased cast-iron skillet.
Sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until done.

title: salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with hot water until dissolved.
Add to fruit cocktail (do not drain fruit).
Put in refrigerator until almost set.
Then add mayonnaise and Cool Whip and mix together.
Can be used as salad or dessert.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed on package.
Mix the Eagle Brand milk with pudding mixture; fold in the Cool Whip.
Line dish with vanilla wafers and bananas.
Alternate with pudding mixture.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream butter, add sugar.
Beat well.
Beat in egg.
Melt chocolate over hot water.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients and add to chocolate mixture alternately with milk. Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.

title: apple harvest cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Generously grease (use 1 tablespoon solid shortening) and flour 12-cup fluted tube pan (nonstick finish pan, too).
Lightly spoon flour in measuring cup; level off.
In large mixer bowl, blend all ingredients until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Add raisins and sweet potatoes.
Combine egg, oil, milk, yogurt, maple syrup and vanilla.
Add to flour mixture and combine gently and quickly.
Coat muffin tins with non stick spray and divide batter evenly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: banana salad
directions: Cook eggs, brown sugar, flour and milk until very thick. Remove from fire and add 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of peanut butter.
Put in container and put in refrigerator until cold. Beat 2 packages of Dream Whip until thick and add the dressing you cooked.
Put one layer of dressing and one layer of bananas until dish is filled.
Cover with ground peanuts.

title: blackberry jam
directions: Wash, rinse, drain and thoroughly crush and measure berries into kettle.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Put kettle over low heat and stir mixture until sugar dissolves; then boil rapidly to or almost to jellying point or until jelly rounds up slightly in spoon.
Remove from heat; quickly skim off foam and pour hot jam into sterilized jars and seal while hot.
Makes 4 to 5 half pints.

title: black pepper-crusted standing rib roast au jus
directions: Boning the roast makes slicing the meat much easier at serving time; have your butcher remove the backbone, or chine, from the whole rack and cut the meat off the ribs in 1 piece. Then tie the meat back onto the bones. The roast can be served on or off the bones. To crack whole peppercorns, enclose them in a resealable plastic bag and crush slightly with a meat mallet.

title: chicken hedgehogs
directions: Place chicken in a food processor or blender with eggs, flour, sugar, soy sauce, sherry and salt.
Blend until smooth paste forms.
Place in bowl.
Cover and chill for 20 minutes.

title: hawaiian-style spareribs
directions: Cut ribs or chicken into serving pieces, trimming off excess fat.
Arrange in pan.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar, catsup and pineapple with juice.
Pour over ribs or chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and beat by hand.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: (You may add another can of mushrooms if desired.)

title: swiss turkey quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pastry shell 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce heat to 350°.
In medium bowl, toss cheese with flour and bouillon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes until set, topping with French fried onions during last 5 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: school pizza burgers
directions: Spread mixture on the half of hamburger bun.
Put cheese strips on.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until cheese is slightly melted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix ingredients in a casserole dish.
Spread evenly and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: diana's cocoa cream pie
directions: Mix cocoa, 1 cup sugar and flour.
Add egg yolks, then milk and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Bake at 350° in a 9-inch pie shell.

title: crisp onion-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven at 450°.
In a shallow baking pan, thoroughly blend all ingredients, except potatoes.
Add potatoes and turn to saturate.
Bake 60 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Stir occasionally.
Garnish, if desired, with chopped parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna fish ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll together to form ball. Roll in parsley flakes and serve with fat-free crackers.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat and onions in small amount of oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients except gravy mix.
Simmer until meat is tender (may need to add extra water).
When meat gets tender, stir in gravy mix and let thicken.
Serve over rice.
(Recipe may be doubled.)

title: coffee cake
directions: Whip egg until light.
Add shortening and milk.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add other ingredients and mix together. Sprinkle topping over cake.

title: hawaiian rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and serve.
Garnish with coconut or a cherry.
For extra flavor, use pineapple syrup or juice as part of the liquid when cooking the rice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: This can be made with ham, crab, pork or turkey.

title: pork chop dinner
directions: Trim fat from pork chops.
Grease large skillet with fat. Cook chops in skillet over medium heat until brown on both sides. Drain off fat.
Sprinkle chops with salt.
Top each chop with one slice of onion.

title: bakers icing(white)
directions: Mix flour and milk until smooth.
Cook slowly, stirring occasionally until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and cool. Add butter and shortening and blend at low speed.
Add salt.
Beat at high speed until smooth and fluffy.
Blend in sugar.
Beat at high speed until sugar crystals dissolve.
Add vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at high speed.

title: shrimp creole and rice
directions: Cook bacon and onion together.
Drain excess grease off.
To the tomato sauce, add sugar, bacon, onion, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut shrimp into bite size pieces and add to sauce.
Pour sauce over rice.
Mix well. Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: nut butter balls
directions: Cream together butter and vanilla; sift in confectioners sugar and pecans. Mix flour in. Form into balls. Place on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 300° until light brown. Drench in additional confectioners sugar.

title: rancho dagwood
directions: Slice French bread lengthwise.
Spread with processed cheese. Brown ground beef until crumbly.
Add salt and spoon over cheese. Sprinkle with green onions, mushrooms and oregano.
Spoon over tomato sauce.
Bake in a very hot 450° oven for 5 minutes.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and corn syrup in a 2-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture turns a light caramel color (290°).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour syrup over popped corn and nuts on baking sheet. Toss with two large spoons until popped corn and nuts are coated. Spread to dry.
Break into pieces and store.

title: crab ball
directions: Combine crab meat and cream cheese.
Form into a ball.
Place ball
on platter and top with cocktail sauce.
Use your favorite crackers to serve crab ball on and to garnish platter.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from fire and add peanut butter, oatmeal and flavoring.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper until firm.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Beat together.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa.
Add to the mixture.
Add cake flour and salt.
Alternate flour and buttermilk.
Add soda and vinegar.
Do not beat; stir.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: maple syrup
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and corn syrup in a saucepan and bring to a boil; cover.
Boil gently 10 minutes or until syrup spins a thread (keeping pan covered prevents formation of crystals around sides of pan).
Add maple flavoring to taste.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch layer pans or one 13x9 in pan.
Blend dry ingredients in bowl.
Add shortening, water, and applesauce.
Beat 2 min, medium speed with mixer. Scrape sides and bottom of bowl constantly.
Add eggs.
Beat 2 more min., scraping bowl frequently.
Stir in walnuts and raisings. Bake layers 35 to 40 min and 13x9 pan 45 to 50 min.
Cool.
Frost with Easy Penuche Frosting.

title: chicken puffs(vegetarian)
directions: Mix cream cheese and margarine; add "Fri Chik," mushrooms and onions. In a separate bowl, mix breadcrumbs and pecan meal. Roll the crescent rolls into squares. Put a heaping tablespoonful of the chicken mixture in each center. Roll up and seal. Dip in melted margarine and roll in nut mixture. Bake at 350°.

title: frosting for kahlua cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cocoa gradually.
Add Kahlua and hot coffee.
Beat and spread.

title: (my mom's) apple cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat sugar and eggs until smooth. Add oil.
Sift dry ingredients into above mixture and mix well. Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Cut into pan.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onions in oleo in skillet until tender.
Add to boiled and drained squash.
Add rest of ingredients except save 1/2 cup of cheese to sprinkle on top.
Pour in greased casserole and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chipped ham barbecue
directions: Brown beef.
Add chopped vegetables, then add other ingredients.
Simmer at least 30 minutes.

title: cream of wild rice soup
directions: Prepare wild rice in large kettle.
Add water, bouillon, meat and evaporated milk.
Heat through, but don't boil.
To thicken, add 1/4 cup cold water and 2 tablespoons cornstarch.

title: egg-bacon-cheese dish
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay pieces of bread along bottom and sprinkle with cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients, except for bacon.
Pour over cheese and bread.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Towards ends of hour, cover with foil if browning too much.
Done when knife inserted comes out clean.
Dish may be covered and chilled up to 24 hours before cooking.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine chicken, 3/4 of soup, 1/2 cup sour cream, green chiles and olives.
Put 2 to 3 tablespoons of chicken mix in middle of tortilla.
Roll and place in shallow, buttered casserole.

title: champagne punch
directions: In large punch bowl, mix together pineapple juice, champagne, wine and pineapple chunks with the juice.
Add ice cubes. Float fruit to garnish.
Makes 6-quarts.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in pie plate or quiche dish.
Spread chili on top.
Then the scallions and finally the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate mint pie(yields 8 servings)
directions: Mix cookies and hot water in small bowl.
Spread evenly in bottom of crust.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth.
Add milk and peppermint extract.
Beat until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping and food coloring.
Spoon mixture into pie crust.
Smooth top with spatula.
Refrigerate 3 hours or until set.
If desired, garnish with whipped topping and maraschino cherries.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Chill.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows over medium heat.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Stir in Rice Krispies, a little at a time. Coat Krispies well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or other suitable dish.
Refrigerate and cut into squares.

title: fruit cocktail salad
directions: Soften cheese and blend with mayonnaise.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into an ice cube tray and freeze overnight or for at least 6 hours.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce. Trim with cherries.
Can also be used as a dessert.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Soften cheese and other ingredients.
Chill. Form in ball and roll in nuts.

title: salmon ball spread
directions: Mix and roll in chopped nuts or chopped parsley; serve with crackers.

title: crab bisque
directions: Blend soups.
Stir in milk and cream; heat just to boiling. Add crab meat; heat thoroughly.
Add cooking sherry just before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: double decker marbled meltaway fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a rapid boil 5 minutes; add peanut butter and creme after removing from heat.
In a heat-proof bowl, mix 1/2 peanut butter mixture and 1 cup chips.
Mix together.
Pour in a baking dish.
Pour rest of peanut mixture on top; then rest of chips.
Let them melt and then swirl together.
Cut into squares.
Refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat the oven to 325°.
Grease a loaf pan, either 9 x 5 x 3-inch or 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch, with shortening.
Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in a large bowl with a wooden spoon.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Add milk to flour.
Bring broth to a boil; add milk/flour mixture.
Add soup and butter.
Cook until thickened.
Cook and drain noodles.
Add noodles to sauce mixture, then add chicken. Pour combined ingredients into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese and corn flakes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grand pate(fried dough)
directions: Sift together the first 3 ingredients.
Mix well. Add water until dough is like biscuit dough. Roll on a floured board and cut in any shape you'd like.
Fry in deep fat or oil until golden brown. Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: grandmother's rolls
directions: Dissolve the lard and sugar in hot water, add egg. When mixture is lukewarm add yeast which has been dissolved in lukewarm water, add flour, salt and beat well. put in refrigerator and let rise 3 to 4 hours. Then take out in rolls what is needed, let rise at least 2 hours and bake. Bake at 425 degrees till golden brown.

title: easy angel food cake dessert
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese together, then fold in Cool Whip. Cut angel food cake in half.
Put the mixture in the middle of the cake and on top of the cake.
Add your favorite fruit topping. The best is cherry or strawberry pie filling in a can.

title: mile high biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles corn meal.
Beat egg and add milk.
Mix in dry ingredients with fork until dough holds together.
Turn on a floured board; knead lightly and roll 1-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter and put on a baking sheet.
Preheat oven to 450° and bake biscuits 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken dressing
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing according to directions.
(I use some of the broth from the chicken for the liquid.) Pour on bottom of a pan 9 x 13 x 2-inches, then top with the chicken.
Then mix water and soup and pour over the chicken and stuffing.
Then sprinkle the crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it is hot, bubbling and a little brown on top.
I cover it with aluminum foil for 20 minutes and then uncover.
Can be prepared the day before you plan to use it.

title: salted peanut chews
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes or until light brown.

title: chocolate logs
directions: Mix together sugar, coconut, pecans, vanilla, cracker crumbs, peanut butter and butter.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Shape first mixture into logs.
Dip logs into paraffin mixture and place on waxed paper to set.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix oleo, powdered sugar, salt and 2 cups of flour.
Dough will be stiff.
Pack into a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Clean carrots and slice into 1/2-inch medallions. Cook them 10 minutes; drain. Combine all other ingredients and bring to a boil that you can't stir down. Pour over carrots. Marinate overnight. Serve cold. Yield: approximately 8 servings.

title: red new potatoes with mustard dressing
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling, salted water about 20 minutes. Drain; cool and cut into quarters.
Place potatoes in a large bowl.
Pour the dressing over the potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Toss carefully, using a large rubber spatula. Sprinkle with scallions and parsley.
Toss to combine.
Be sure to cover the potatoes with plenty of dressing as the potatoes absorb it quickly.

title: butter cream frosting
directions: Blend together until smooth, then spread on cake.

title: campfire foil dinner
directions: Lay choice of meat on heavy duty foil.
Cover with slices of potatoes, carrots and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Wrap in foil.
Cook 20-30 minutes over hot coals. Turn twice during cooking.

title: cool whip delight
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a large bowl. Serve.

title: deluxe garlic bread
directions: Trim all crust from bread and slice in half lengthwise.
Mix butter and dressing mix.
Spread on all sides of bread.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch as it burns easily.

title: jean arp hugeback rye bread
directions: 5 - 6 cups warm water mixes together the yeast and sugar until yeast starts to work.
Then add:
rye flour, salt and white flour.
Enough to make dough stiff.
Knead dough till its not sticky.
Put into pans.
Let rise.
Bake 1 hour.

title: mabel (dodge) kerr's date bars
directions: Mix oatmeal, flour, butter, sugar and soda like pie crust. Grease cake pan and cover with half of the crumbs.
Cook dates, brown sugar and milk until thick.
Spread filling over crumbs. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Pour into ice cream freezer and finish filling up to fill line with plain milk. Stir well and freeze.

title: cold oven cake
directions: Cream the sugar, shortening and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour. Add salt and baking powder gradually with milk and flavoring.
Grease a
10-inch tube pan and put cake in cold oven. Turn to bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes, then check.

title: dutch style meat loaf(low-fat)
directions: Combine tomato sauce, water, mustard and vinegar.

Mix veal with bread crumbs, egg, onion, pepper and 1/4 of tomato sauce mixture. Shape into a loaf pan. Pour enough of the sauce over the top of loaf to coat. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting often. Serve remaining sauce heated over sliced meat loaf.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Place rhubarb in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine eggs, 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, milk and oil.
Pour over rhubarb.
Sprinkle with remaining cup of sugar.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: louisiana pecan pie
directions: Place sugar and syrup in heavy saucepan over medium heat and cook until thick, about 15 minutes.
Add butter and flavorings; stir.
Blend in eggs with pastry whip.
Eggs must be blended quickly into hot sugar mixture.
Add pecans; pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 300° until pie shell is golden brown.

title: 1-2-3-4 layer cake
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Separate the egg yolks.
Add to butter and sugar mixture.
Beat egg whites; set aside.
Add flour and milk gradually.
Add the remaining ingredients and beat.

title: pizza crust
directions: In large mixer bowl, stir together 2 1/2 cups flour, yeast and salt.
Add warm water and oil.
