Beat on low speed of electric mixer 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Pat hamburg in a 10-inch pie plate like you're making a crust; broil until half done. Drain grease.
Heat onion, celery and green pepper in microwave. Drain and put into "crust."
Heat frozen corn and mushrooms in microwave.
Drain and put into "crust."
Mix the mushroom soup and garlic.
Pour over all. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Make up instant mashed potatoes and cover top.
Sprinkle with paprika and/or shredded Cheddar cheese. Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate icing deluxe
directions: Mix all ingredients together; beat with rotary beater until fluffy.
Icing for 2 layer cake.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: Combine sugar and flour; stir in 3 tablespoons pineapple juice; add pineapple and cheese. Mix well and place into 1 quart baking dish. Combine butter and cracker crumbs; sprinkle on top of pineapple mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Pour all together and serve chilled.

title: roast leg of lamb with herbed mustard glaze
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place leg of lamb on rack in shallow baking pan.
Roast for 1 hour.

title: brazilian coffee cookies
directions: Mix altogether, then add to milk.
Make into 1-inch ball. Flatten by hand.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: leisers cucumbers
directions: Heat vinegar and sugar to boil.
Cool.
Slice cucumbers and onions.
Soak in salt water for 3 hours.
Squeeze salt solution out of cucumbers.
Add garlic buds.
Pour cooled syrup over cucumbers.
Store in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Will stay a long time in refrigerator.

title: chocolate-coconut kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in sugar. Continue beating until mixture is very stiff and glossy.
Stir in salt, vanilla, coconut and melted but slightly cooled chocolate. Drop heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased wrapping paper on cookie sheet.
Bake about 20 minutes at 325°.
Bake until set and delicately browned.
Makes about 3 dozen Kisses.

title: rock cornish hens with grapes
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add salt and pepper.
Split hens; place skin side up in shallow baking pan.
Baste with margarine. Roast hens for 1 1/2 hours uncovered.
When done, pour pan drippings into small saucepan.
Add chicken broth and grape juice. Simmer 15 minutes until reduced to 1 cup.
Add grapes; cook 2 minutes.
Calories:

title: ayers corn bread
directions: Put grease in pan and melt.
Combine all other ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix sugar, rhubarb and pineapple; cook for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in jello.
Pour in jars and cover with Parowax.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Place cream cheese in 1-quart casserole.
Heat in microwave until melted.
Stir halfway through melting.
Stir in soup and onions.
Heat in microwave until bubbly, stirring halfway through cooking time, about 3 minutes.
Serve warm as dip or with raw vegetables.

title: dilled alaskan garden medley
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add vegetables.
Cook and stir 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in dill and salt.
Reduce heat; cover and cook 2 to 3 minutes longer until vegetables are tender.
Makes 7 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: lenten borscht
directions: Add vegetables to boiling water.
Those vegetables which take longer to
cook should be added first and cooked for a while before adding the others.
Cook until tender.
In 4 tablespoons of oil, fry onion (diced) until lightly browned. Add 2 tablespoons of flour until it thickens.
Add to soup.
Cook for a few minutes longer.

title: creamy onion soup
directions: In a large saucepan bring to a boil the onions, carrot, bouillon cube and water.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Add milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Blend flour and 1/2 cup of water until smooth.
Stir into soup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Add the 1/2 cup milk and margarine; stir until margarine is melted.
Serve.

title: fast spaghetti
directions: Cook together in a frying pan.
Cook spaghetti.
Pour meat over it.
Garnish with cheese.

title: parmesan nibble squares(microwave)
directions: In an 8-inch square glass dish, combine margarine and garlic powder.
Micromelt the margarine 30 to 40 seconds.
Stir in rice or corn squares until coated with margarine mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Microcook, uncovered, about 3 minutes on High, stirring twice.
Cool.
Makes 2 cups.

title: cabbage cacciatore
directions: In ovenproof skillet, brown meat and onions. Pour sauce over all.
Cover and cook in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on casserole and return to oven for 5 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: lois' delight
directions: Brown meat and drain; add spaghetti sauce.
Cook noodles in boiling water.
While noodles are cooking, mix cream cheese, sour cream and chopped onions.
After meat and noodles are cooked, mix all other ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add one can soup (undiluted) to beef.
If necessary, soften tortillas in frying pan with hot oil folding 1/3 of top down.
Remove from oil when soft.
Fill each tortilla with small amount of beef mixture and grated cheese.
Roll and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining cheese.
Heat other can of soup and 1/2 soup can water.
Add chili powder.

title: pluckett cake
directions: Mix
sugar,
cinnamon and brown sugar.	Cut biscuits in fours. Place sugar in bag.
Put biscuits in bag.	Shake well. Place half
of biscuits in tube pan.
Pour half of the melted butter and
half
of the pecans on the biscuits.
Add rest of biscuits, butter
and
pecans.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Do not
cut
this cake.
Pluckett while it is still warm or just out of the oven.

title: old world dumplings(german)
directions: Put peeled potatoes in boiling soup and boil until done. Remove to bowl and mash.
Add salt and oleo to taste.
May also add nutmeg to taste at this time.
Allow to cool.
Add the unbeaten egg and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Drop by spoon into boiling soup.
To make them easier to drop, dip spoon in soup, then scoop dough to drop.
Continue cooking for a short time until done, but not falling apart.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Drain juice from clams; reserve.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil and butter in saucepan until tender but not brown.
Add reserved clam juice, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil on high heat.
Cook until reduced to 1 cup, approximately 5 minutes. Meanwhile, cook and drain linguine.
Keep hot.
Reduce heat under clam juice mixture; add reserved clams, parsley, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Heat thoroughly.
Toss with hot linguine.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to a boil.
Pour over browned salted and peppered meat and let simmer.

title: lillie's crab au gratin
directions: Blend flour, salt and pepper with melted margarine.
Add milk; cook until smooth and thick.
Add 1 1/4 cups of grated cheese (reserve 1/4 cup for topping).
Blend well.
In a casserole dish alternate thin layers of cheese sauce and crab meat.
Start layers with cheese sauce.
Mix remaining cheese and cracker crumbs together.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 375° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: hermits
directions: Beat butter until soft.
Gradually add brown sugar, egg and buttermilk.
Combine and sift flour, cinnamon, cloves and baking soda. Add to mixture.
Beat to smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and drop batter on cookie sheet. Bake about 15 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix grated cheese, tomatoes, green onions and broken up head lettuce.
Brown
and
season
with	salt
and pepper, the ground beef.
Add	oregano.
Add drained kidney beans and taco seasonings (follow
directions
on
package).
When
ready to serve, mix first the cheese mixture, then the ground beef and then add dressing and corn chips.

title: brandy slush
directions: Heat water and sugar until dissolved.
Add lemonade and orange juice.
Add 1 cup or more of brandy.
Pour into ice cream bucket and freeze.
Before serving, add 7-Up in glass with slush.

title: spiced pears
directions: You also need a 1-quart jar (an empty mayonnaise or salad dressing jar is perfect).

title: carmen's potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except potatoes.
Mix potatoes in last.

title: triple berry margaritas(bon appetit; 8 to 10 servings.)
directions: Puree the blackberries, raspberries and lime juice in blender until smooth (approximately 4 cups).
Strain through a fine mesh strainer into a large measuring cup (or use a Foley's food mill). Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Refrigerate berry puree at least 1 hour and up to 1 day.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs with mixer.
Add next three ingredients; beat until thick and foamy.
Stir the next two ingredients with a spoon. Combine the rest of the ingredients and then mix all ingredients together and stir.
Bake in loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Turn out on racks.

title: corn pudding
directions: Stir together the first six ingredients until well blended. Stir in corn.
Pour into a lightly greased 1
1/2 quart baking dish.
Before baking sprinkle the top liberally with breadcrumbs and spray with Pam.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until set.
Let stand five minutes.

title: cookies and cream pie
directions: Pour half and half into large bowl.
Add pie filling mix. Beat until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping and crushed cookies.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, approximately 6 hours or overnight.
Remove from freezer and let stand 10 minutes to soften before serving.
Store any leftovers in freezer.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, butter, egg and vanilla.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Drop dough from rounded teaspoonful on to ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all above ingredients. Drained most all beans and then very LIGHTLY rinse them under water.

title: filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Stir in chocolate pieces.
Drop one rounded teaspoonful into each cupcake.
Bake as package directs.
Makes about 30 cupcakes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except ketchup.
Shape in baking dish.
Put the ketchup on top.
Cook on Medium-high (70%) for 22 minutes.
Allow to stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.

title: great, great grandma's crazy cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients into 9 x 9 baking pan. Make 3 holes in dry ingredients. In first hole, put oil. In second hole, put vinegar. In third hole, put vanilla. Pour cold water over all. Stir well with fork. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. May serve with butter or following icing.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix sugar and jello in hot water.
Grind other ingredients, except nuts and add to jello.
Add nuts and chill until set.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, spices and nuts; set aside.
Beat eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until creamy.
Add zucchini and pineapple, mixing well.
Stir in dry ingredients, just until moistened.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pans, then turn on racks and cool.

title: swiss cheese chicken
directions: Grease bottom of pan.
Place chicken in pan.
Mix soup and wine, pour over chicken.
Place six slices of cheese on top. Sprinkle with stuffing.
Pour butter over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
(It takes a while.)
Pour into two (8-inch) graham cracker crusts or 1 (9-inch) pie crust.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: In small mixing bowl, beat egg and buttermilk.
Mix in all other ingredients and stir well.
Spoon batter into 6 paper lined custard cups or microproof muffin pan.
Fill about half full.
Cook 6 muffins at a time on High (Maximum power), 2 to 3 minutes or until no longer doughy.
Repeat twice.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: zucchini nut bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Sift together flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs well.
Gradually add sugar and oil, mixing well.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients; blend well.
Stir in zucchini.
Combine nuts with 1 teaspoon flour; stir into batter. Pour into loaf pans.
Sprinkle on topping.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: old fashioned 3 pound fruit cake
directions: Cream butter, mixing until smooth.
Add brown sugar, beating well.
Add eggs and mix.
Then add sifted dry ingredients alternately with water, beating well after each addition.
(Hold in reserve 1/2 cup flour for dredging fruit and nuts before adding to above mixture.)

Combine the 1/2 cup flour with the fruit. Then fold in the fruit, nuts and molasses to the butter mixture. Pour into pan which has been well greased and lined with wax paper. Bake in oven 275° for 2 to 3 hours.
A pan of water placed in oven while cake is baking adds moisture to cake.

title: hot pizza dip
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and Italian seasoning. Spread in an ungreased 9-inch microwave-safe pie plate. Combine Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses. Sprinkle half over cream cheese. Top with the pizza sauce, remaining cheese mixture, green pepper and onion. Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, uncovered, or until the cheese is almost melted. (Rotate a half turn several times.) Let stand for 1 to 2 minutes. Yields about 3 cups. Serve with tortilla chips or breadsticks.

title: fudge cake pudding
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa.
Stir together milk, vanilla and melted shortening; add to dry ingredients.
Add nuts and pour into greased 9x
13-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar and 8 tablespoons cocoa and sprinkle over batter. Pour hot water over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: range top lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain.
Place ground beef in Dutch oven and sprinkle with 1 package spaghetti mix; spread half cottage cheese over meat.
Break noodles in half lengthwise; layer over cottage cheese.
Sprinkle with other package of spaghetti mix, Italian seasoning, parsley and salt.
Pour tomatoes, tomato sauce and water over mixture.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 35 minutes or until noodles are tender. Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella over top.
Cover and turn off heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, cook slowly until mixture thickens.
Cool!
Add all but Cool Whip, mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip and freeze.
Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water, then add the oil, salt, sugar and 3 1/2 cups of flour.
Mix well.
Then add other 3 cups of flour; mix well.

title: walking tostido dip
directions: Layer ingredients in order.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours to let ingredients settle.

title: tropical turkey salad
directions: Combine turkey, water chestnuts, grapes, celery and 2 cups almonds.
Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice. Combine with turkey mixture.
Spoon onto bed of lettuce.
Garnish with remaining almonds and pineapple.
Chicken may be substituted for turkey.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: oreo "dirt" cake
directions: Crush Oreos in large bowl. In another bowl, pour pudding mix and milk. Mix on high speed for 2 minutes. Then add Cool Whip and cream cheese a little bit at a time until well blended. Pour cookie crumbs in bottom of dish. Pour in all pudding mix; spread to edges. Add rest of cookie crumbs on top.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt.
Coat with egg and then with cornstarch.
Brown in hot oil until brown.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine sugar, vinegar, ketchup, bouillon and soy sauce in medium pan.
Bring mixture to boil.
Pour over chicken. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt margarine in heavy pot.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Stir and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop or spread onto waxed paper.

title: browned rice
directions: Melt butter.
Add rice and onion.
Cook until lightly browned in a frypan.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in hot water.
Add half the liquid; cover and cook on low heat.
Add rest of the liquid, stirring occasionally.
Takes about 45 minutes to cook.

title: veal scallopini
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; dust veal lightly with flour mixture.
In medium skillet, brown meat slowly in hot oil.
Add onion to same skillet; cook until tender but not brown.
Add brown tomatoes (undrained), mushrooms, capers, garlic salt and oregano. Cover; simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Arrange veal on hot buttered noodles; top with sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: omelet souffle
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually add sugar, then flour.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites stiff and gently fold into yolk mixture.
Heat butter in skillet.
Let it cover all of skillet and be very hot.
Pour the omelet mix and bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
The omelet should slide out easily by tipping the skillet.
Serve with peaches, apricots, or your choice.

title: candied pop corn
directions: Melt oleo; stir in sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: In a skillet, brown and crumble sausage; drain and set aside. In a large bowl, beat eggs. Add milk, salt and mustard. Stir in bread cubes, cheese and sausage. Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2 baking dish. Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight. Remove from the refrigerator 30 minutes before baking. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: pineapple-carrot jam
directions: Bring all ingredients, except lemon juice, to a boil in a 2-quart saucepan.
Reduce heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture is thick as applesauce and pineapple is translucent.
Stir in lemon juice.
Pack into hot jars, cover completely, cool and refrigerate.
Makes 4 cups.

title: huluski mom's way
directions: Mix first four ingredients together until thick.
Boil water. Add dumplings by teaspoonful.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Dice 1/2 head of cabbage and saute in 1/2 cup margarine.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar.
Simmer until cabbage is tender.
Pour over drained dumplings.
Serve.

title: baked potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes.
Slice potatoes in half.
Scoop out pulp, reserving skins.
Deep fry skins for 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Place in baking sheet.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve with mixture of sour cream and chives.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind all the vegetables.
Put the salt over ground vegetables and let stand for 2 hours.
Drain and add vinegar and sugar.
Cook until tender, then cool.
Add salad dressing and mustard.
This doesn't need to be sealed.

title: dumplings
directions: Combine.
Drop by small spoonful in hot broth.
Cover; do not boil liquid and do not take cover off until done.
It takes about 20 minutes for them to cook.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make a crust with the graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Beat the powdered sugar, egg, soft butter, vanilla and cream cheese for 15 minutes and spread over crust.
Chill.
Spoon the pineapple over the crust.
Place the sliced bananas in the pineapple juice.
Drain and spread over the pineapple.
Ice with the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with the chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: cowboy beans
directions: In skillet brown ground beef, onions and sweet pepper.
Drain. Put in crock-pot.
Add barbecue sauce, ketchup and beans.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream sugar and oleo; add salt and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, buttermilk and baking soda. Pour in buttermilk while beating everything so ingredients will be moist.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: frozen orange dessert
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and set aside 3/4 cups.
Press remaining into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine sweetened condensed milk and orange juice.
Fold in whipped topping and oranges.
Spoon over crust, sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture. Cover and freeze.

title: jalapeno soy dip(china)
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Place in covered bowl and refrigerate for 2 hours. Serves well with veggie slices, crackers or chips. Makes 2 cups.

title: honey baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Combine margarine, honey, mustard, salt and curry powder. Mix well.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Baste every 15 minutes. Brown well.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage leaves (approximately 6) until tender, drain and set aside.
Blend all other ingredients, except tomato juice, then form into shapes to accomodate cabbage leaves.
Wrap meat mixture balls with cabbage leaves and place in pan.
Pour tomato juice over the ingredients.
Cover pan with lid or foil.
Bake at 350° about two hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix well; store in refrigerator.

title: beer bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: easy parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine soup mixes, cheese, potatoes and oil.
(The oil may be substituted with Pam. Spray Pam on casserole dish and on potato mixture.)
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain well.
Rinse with cold water.
Add pepper, tomato and onion.
Pour 1/2 bottle of Seven Seas red wine salad vinegar over and mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Place in casserole dish.
Makes a beautiful and healthy dish.

title: italian fare for four
directions: Brown loin chops in iron skillet sprayed with Pam to avoid sticking.
Remove from skillet when partially cooked.
Drain off any grease.
Pour spaghetti sauce into skillet; add spices to taste.
Add green beans and mix gently.
Replace loin chops. Sprinkle cheese over all.
Cover.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: my mom's best rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add sugar, eggs, warm water, and oil.
Mix salt into flour and add to batter.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and let dough rise 8 hours.
Knead dough and shape into crescent shaped rolls.
Let rise another 8 hours or overnight on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sal's pasta ala vodka
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
(Add while oil is still cool.)
Add Prosciutto; saute about 10 minutes, until onion is translucent.
Add butter, chopped pepper, sun-dried tomatoes, hot pepper flakes and basil; simmer 10 minutes.
Add heavy cream, grated cheese, vodka, artichoke hearts and just enough prepared sauce until sauce is pink color.
Serve over bow tie pasta.

title: wilted spinach with fragrant mushrooms
directions: Spray 10-inch nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray. Cook onion, garlic and broth in skillet over medium-high heat for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally until liquid has evaporated.
Stir in mushrooms, wine and tomato paste. Cook over medium-high heat for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in spinach, green onions and parsley.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, stirring occasionally until spinach is wilted.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Yields 6 servings.

title: candy cane cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Beat cake mix with water, oil, egg whites and extract in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl frequently, 2 minutes.
Pour about 2 cups batter into pan.
Pour about 3/4 cup batter into small bowl.
Stir in food coloring.
Carefully pour pink batter over white batter in pan.
Pour remaining batter carefully over pink batter.
Bake until cake pulls away from sides of pan and springs back when touched in center, 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Invert on serving plate.
After cake cools completely, spread with Creamy Glaze.

title: fruit ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into a ball.
Refrigerate until firm.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: gayle's key lime pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and milk until blended.
Add lime juice, vanilla and beaten egg yolks.
Add few drops green food coloring. Beat well.	Pour in graham crust and chill 3 hours.
To serve, cover top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Add buttermilk and jam.
Mix well.
Mix soda and flour and add nuts, raisins and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
(It will be thick.)
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: misty's peanut butter unbaked goodies
directions: In a saucepan put sugar and syrup.
Bring to a boil until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until are mixed well.
Add coconut and corn flakes. Stir until coated good.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Place cooked rice on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Pour cooked chicken (diced or shredded) over rice.
Mix soups and mayonnaise and pour over chicken.
Spread cooked broccoli evenly over the top and sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger tomato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use tomatoes held at room temperature until fully ripe.
Slice four of the tomatoes; chop remaining 2 tomatoes; set aside.
In a large skillet, heat oil.
Add onion. Saute until tender, about 2 minutes.
Add beef.
Saute until browned, about 3 minutes.
Stir in reserved chopped tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, salt and oregano.
Grease casserole dish and spoon half the meat mixture into bottom of the casserole.
Top with half the rice and half the reserved sliced tomatoes.
Repeat, ending with tomatoes.
Brush with butter.
Bake until hot, about 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
This kitchen tested recipe makes 6 servings.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough milk to moisten. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Meatballs cook at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: creamy brussels sprouts
directions: Combine cheese and mayonnaise, stirring until smooth.
Add lemon juice and garlic salt.
Stir in sour cream; mix well. Cover and chill overnight.
To serve, cook Brussels sprouts according to package directions; drain.
Warm the sour cream mixture in top of double boiler; add cooked Brussels sprouts. Serve immediately.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: caramel-filled chocolate cookies(won the pillsbury cookie contest)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup. Level off.
In a small bowl combine flour, cocoa and baking soda. Blend well.

title: pink delight
directions: Mix all together and let set at least 2 hours in refrigerator. Cut into squares to serve.
Top with crushed fresh strawberries.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix together. Spread on 6 split English Muffins.
Makes 12 pieces.
Broil on highest rack till bubbly and slightly brown.
Watch closely.
Cut in quarters and serve hot. You can make these ahead and freeze them then cut in quarters.

title: marmacetti
directions: To 1 tablespoon butter and a little water, add onion and cook slightly.
Add ground pork.
Cook with onion, but don't brown. Add tomato soup, tomato juice, sugar, paprika, salt and pepper. Cook 10 minutes.
Boil noodles and drain.
Mix meat mixture and noodles together.
Mix grated cheese through ingredients. Sprinkle some on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 10 servings.

title: tuna dip
directions: Base:
Mix cottage cheese with enough milk for a smooth and creamy consistency.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Make about 2 cups, then add a mixture of 1 can (6 3/4 ounce) tuna (drained), 1 teaspoon dill weed and 1 teaspoon lemon juice.
Chill before serving.

title: sue's biscuits
directions: Put buttermilk in bowl first, then add oil, baking powder and flour.
Just add enough flour so it won't be sticky.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute the onions in the butter.
Pour onions into bowl.
Mix into thawed broccoli and then mix in the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake for 1 hour.

title: fondant stuffed dates
directions: Gradually add sugar to milk.
When well blended, add vanilla. Mix to a smooth rich ball.
Shape into balls and roll in tinted coconut (red and green).
Use to stuff dates.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese. Carefully stir in pineapple, 1 cup pecans, green pepper, onion and salt.
Chill well and then form into a ball. Roll in remaining cup of pecans.
Makes 8 servings.

title: nappa cabbage salad
directions: Tear cabbage into pieces.
Slice green onions and toss with cabbage.
In blender, mix together vinegar, oil, soy sauce and sugar.
In small skillet, brown almonds and Ramen noodles (broken into small pieces) in small amount of oil on low heat.
Stir.
Add sesame seed.
Set aside to cool.
Add to cabbage mixture when cooled.
Toss with dressing that is in blender.

title: creamy vanilla pudding
directions: In a medium size glass bowl, combine cornstarch and sugar. With a whisk, gradually stir milk into the cornstarch mixture. Cook in microwave on High power for 5 to 7 minutes or until thickened and bubbling, stirring after each 2 minute interval. Beat half of the hot mixture into the eggs.
Blend egg mixture into remaining hot mixture.
Microwave on High power for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until thickened and heated through, stirring after each 45 seconds of cooking.
With whisk, stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into dessert dishes.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover bottom with cooked chicken. With whisk, mix together the sour cream, mushroom soup and the chicken broth.
Ladle over chicken.

title: cherry-o cream cheese pie
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until softened. Beat until fluffy.
Gradually add sweetened condensed milk while stirring.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add lemon juice and vanilla extract.
Stir until well mixed.
Turn mixture onto prepared crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours in refrigerator.
Do not freeze.

title: cheese ring
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Butter Tupperware mold.
Put cheese mixture in mold; mash down and make even.
Chill at least 24 hours.
Put mold in hot water in sink and unmold quickly.
Pour strawberry preserves into middle of Cheese Ring. If desired, put fresh strawberries around the ring.
Serve with crackers.
Place cheese mixture and preserves on each cracker when served.

title: coffee cake
directions: Spray bundt pan with Pam.
Sprinkle bottom with 1/4 cup pecans.
Place frozen rolls on nuts.
Mix brown sugar, pudding and cinnamon and pour over rolls.
Melt butter and pour over top of rolls.
Top with pecans.
Take a damp cloth and cover the top. Place in a cold oven and leave overnight.
In the morning, remove the cloth and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.	Remove from bundt pan. Ice with powdered sugar and milk drizzled over warm ring.

title: greek salad
directions: Break lettuce into a large bowl.
Add tomatoes, cucumbers, radishes, onions, green pepper, parsley and olives.
Toss lightly. Add Feta cheese; sprinkle with Oil-Vinegar Dressing.
Toss lightly again.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in greased pan.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce over chops.
Sprinkle rice over all chops.
Peel and cut up potatoes and carrots; place over chops.
Salt and pepper to taste. Cut up onion and pepper in strips; put on top.
Pour peeled tomatoes and juice over all ingredients.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours, covered, on low heat.
Add extra liquid if needed.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer in a large glass bowl:
3 cups lettuce, sugar, eggs, peas, salt, pepper, 3 cups lettuce, carrots, Swiss cheese, mayo, green onion and paprika.
Cover.
Chill 24 hours.
Toss when serving.

title: party punch
directions: Combine chilled juices.
Mix sugar with lemon juice until dissolved.
Blend well.
Before serving, add chilled ginger ale and softened sherbet.
Makes 40 one-half cup servings.

title: pineapple dish
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased 8-inch baking dish.
Spread pineapple chunks over batter.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and pineapple juice 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spread over pineapple to within 1-inch edge of dish.
Stir together 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello and pineapple in 2 cups of hot water.
Mix blueberry pie filling in.
Let gel.

title: louisiana yam pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon and mix with eggs; add margarine and mashed yams.
Mix and add lemon extract and milk, mixing well at all times.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce to 375° and cook 30 minutes.

title: low-fat fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic and saute 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring with a wire wisk until blended.
Cook 8 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring constantly.
Stir in cream cheese; cook 2 minutes. Add 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, stirring constantly until it melts. Pour over hot, cooked fettucine; toss well to coat.
Top with remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, fresh parsley and pepper.
One cup contains 7 grams of fat.

title: white sauce or cheese sauce for vegetables
directions: In medium saucepan, slowly heat butter just until melted and golden, not browned, stirring all the while. Remove from heat. Add flour, salt and pepper; stir until smooth. Add milk, a small amount at a time, stirring after each addition. Return to heat. Over medium heat, bring to boil, stirring constantly. Reduce heat; simmer 1 minute. Add mustard and grated cheese; stir over low heat just until cheese is melted and sauce is hot. Serve over such vegetables as broccoli, asparagus, cauliflower or potatoes.

title: soft peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butters, sugars, egg and vanilla together.
Blend dry ingredients in.
Shape rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into balls; roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes, then remove from oven and flatten dough with fork. Return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes.

title: apple pie filling for canning
directions: Peel and slice enough apples to fill 7 quarts; pack loosely. Boil first 5 ingredients, stirring constantly for 5 minutes.
Add lemon juice and salt.
Pour over apples in jars.
Place lids on jars.
Pressure 10 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.

title: meat loaf teriyaki
directions: Combine all ingredients; blend well.
Cook in loaf pan at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Mix and spoon on parsley, ginger and soy sauce.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Place sauerkraut, onion, pepper and celery in large bowl. Combine sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables. Mix well.
Chill.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 3 minutes. Gradually add sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice. Stir remaining ingredients. Fold this mixture into first mixture. Pour into 18 x 10 x 1 greased and floured pan with 1 cup pecans in bottom. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. With powdered sugar on towel, roll until cool.

title: soybean brittle
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in 3-quart saucepan.
Mix well. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves. Cook, stirring frequently, until mixture turns a light amber color.
Remove from heat; stir in soybeans and margarine.
Return to heat and blend well.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and soda; stir quickly to blend.
Mixture will foam.
Pour onto 2 large greased baking sheets; spread out thin.
Cool thoroughly; break into pieces.
Yields about 2 pounds.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Lightly flour your pizza dough.
Stretch, mold, and manipulate your dough into a 16-inch circle approximately 1/8-inch thick.
Spread spaghetti sauce evenly over dough.
Top with your steamed vegetables and top vegetables with shredded cheese.
Place in a 500°F. preheated oven.
(For best results use a pizza stone.)

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Blend ingredients and cook in a greased, paper-lined tube cake pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peachy cream cheese pie(microwave)
directions: In medium bowl, mix wafer crumbs, walnuts and 1 tablespoon sugar; add melted butter.
Toss to mix well.
Spread mixture evenly into a 9-inch microwave-safe pie plate.
Press onto bottom and up the sides of pie plate.
Microcook on 100% power (High) for 2 minutes or until set.
Cool completely on a wire rack.

title: buckwheat cakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Store in the freezer and take out what is needed for a meal. Add liquids and bake on a hot griddle. Can be doubled 4-5 times to store in the freezer.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Premeasure needed peanut butter and oats; set nearby.
Lay out wax paper.
Melt butter in a small pot.
Add sugar and cocoa; mix well.
Add evaporated milk and mix.
Heat over medium flame.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute exactly, constantly stirring. Add peanut butter and oats; mix quickly.
Mix and drop teaspoonfuls quickly onto wax paper.
Let cool and harden.

title: mock streusel(makes 40 pieces)
directions: Combine.
Divide mixture into four equal parts.
Sprinkle mixture over four rectangles, then roll up each as for jelly roll and place on greased, floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for one hour.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
When cool, cut each roll into 10 pieces.
(Can be frozen.)

title: apple-kissed chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Sprinkle chicken with poultry seasoning. Coat a large skillet with cooking spray.
Place over medium heat.
Add chicken and cook 5 min. on each side or until browned. Remove chicken; drain on paper towels. Return chicken to skillet.
Pour apple juice mixture over chicken, top with onion slices.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Add apples wedges, cover simmer another 10 min., or until chicken is tender.
Transfer chicken mixture to serving platter, using a slotted spoon.
Dissolve cornstarch in water, add to apple juice mixture in skillet, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened.
Spoon sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Mix together until smooth; fold in 1 cup blueberries.
Bake in greased bread pan 30 minutes at 350°.
Double recipe for two loaves.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken with walnuts
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch pieces.
Set aside.
In small bowl, blend soy sauce into cornstarch.
Stir in dry sherry, ginger root, sugar, salt and red pepper.
Set aside.

title: rice balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into golf ball sizes.
Fry or cook, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Soak cabbage in ice water for 2 hours to make crisp; drain. Mix vinegar, water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Mix all ingredients and chill.
Drain to serve.
Make a couple of days ahead for better flavor.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 35 minutes and let cool before cutting.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix condensed milk and lemonade. Gently stir in Cool Whip. Pour in baked pie shell or graham cracker crust and chill 2 hours.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix with hands.
Pour in a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk and boil for 3 minutes.
Take off stove; beat in peanut butter, cocoa, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Add the oatmeal and more if needed.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut cherries, pineapple and dates.
Add broken walnuts.
Mix in milk and add coconut.
Mix well and bake in 250° oven for 1 1/2 hours in a tube pan.
Spray pan well.

title: grape fruit punch
directions: Make a syrup of sugar and water.
Pour in orange and lemon peels from which juice has been removed. Chill.
Remove fruit peels and add other ingredients.
Pour over ice in punch bowl. Makes 6 quarts.

title: cheese grits
directions: Beat and set aside the first 4 ingredients.
Combine in a saucepan the grits, water and butter/margarine.
Cook over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Mix the hot gris with the Cheddar cheese. Stir in egg mixture, mixing well.
Turn into greased 3-quart baking dish.
Bake in low oven at 330° for 45 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dilled shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients and add shrimp.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with toothpicks.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut meat in thin strips.
Toss in flour, salt and pepper. Brown meat and onions in 3 tablespoons hot fat.
Add tomato juice, consomme and sugar.
Reduce heat and simmer until meat is tender. Blend in sour cream, mushrooms and wine.
Heat, but do not boil. Serve over buttered noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: dairy meat casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper in butter.
Add tomato sauce and seasonings.
In separate bowl combine cream cheese, sour cream, cottage cheese and olives (mix in blender).
Line casserole with half of cooked noodles.
Top with cheese mixture.
Cover with remaining noodles and top with meat mixture.
Bake in 2-quart casserole for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger meat, then drain.
Add other ingredients as listed, stirring and mixing ingredients as you add them.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Double recipe if you have large family.

title: fresh lemon filling
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, stir sugar, lemon peel and juice, cornstarch, salt and 1/2 cup water, until blended.
Over medium heat, cook until mixture is very thick and boils briskly, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in butter.
Cool at room temperature.
(If mixture becomes too thick, stir until of spreading consistency.)
Fills 2 cakes.

title: twinkie delight
directions: Make pudding using only 1/2 of the milk called for in directions.
Combine with whipped topping and condensed milk.
Cut Twinkies in half and place cream side up in a dish.
Pour pudding mixture over Twinkies.
Cover with sliced strawberries.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Pasta:
Cook pasta with oil and salt.
Drain and cool.

title: pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Grease heated griddle on Silverstone skillet.
To test temperature, sprinkle with a few drops of water. If water bubbles and skitters around, heat is just right.

title: apple cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add topping before baking.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Soak raisins in hot water 5 minutes; drain.
Combine raisins, broccoli, grapes and green onions in large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and vinegar; stir into broccoli mixture.
Cover and chill.
Stir in almonds and bacon just before serving.

title: buckeyes
directions: Thoroughly mix powdered sugar, crunchy peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Chill to set up.
Roll into small balls.
Insert a toothpick into chilled ball and dip halfway into melted chocolate. Set on wax paper to harden.

title: salsa vinaigrette
directions: Mix together tomato, onion, jalapeno, lime juice and salt to taste.
With motor running, add oil in a stream.
Stir coriander in vinaigrette.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Saute onion and hamburger.
Drain and add cheese.
Mix well. Pour mixture into pie shells that have been cooked according to package directions.

title: squash relish
directions: Sprinkle salt over the squash and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, rinse and drain.
Add the vinegar, celery seed and turmeric to the vegetables and sugar; bring to a boil. Pour into scalded jars and seal. Do not cook squash.
The straight neck yellow squash works best.
May be opened immediately.

title: chicken pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Can use 3 boiled eggs.

title: red cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste of coloring and cocoa; add to shortening mixture.
Add milk alternately with flour and salt.
Add vanilla.
Fold in vinegar and soda (made in a paste).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 2 nine-inch layer pans.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together Crisco and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Mix flour, salt, soda and baking powder together.
Add to Crisco and sugar mixture and mix until blended.
Chill at least 3 hours. Roll out and cut.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Makes 6 dozen.
Can be left to chill overnight.

title: rebel cake
directions: Boil together with sugar, water, lard, salt, raisins and spices for 5 minutes.
When cold, add flour and soda, dissolved in a teaspoon of hot water.
This makes 2 loaves.
Bake about 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in iron skillet over medium heat.
Add peanuts; continue to cook over medium heat, stirring frequently. Cook until peanuts are completely coated.
Pour onto ungreased cookie sheet; separate peanuts with a fork.
Bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes, stirring at 10-minute intervals.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: ranch house casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except biscuits, butter and cornmeal. Place in a shallow 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Dip biscuits in melted butter, then cornmeal. Arrange on casserole.
Bake again 20 to 25 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Spread light mayonnaise (about 2 cups) on top.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bacon bits on top.
When ready to serve, mix well.

title: choclate chip delight
directions: Dip cookies in milk and place in bottom of pan.
Cover with cool whip.
Layer cookies and cool whip until the pan is full.
Let set in refridgerator over night.

title: crab croquettes
directions: Add flour to melted butter.
Add milk; heat until thick.
Add salt and pepper.

title: zucchini fritters
directions: In colander, mix zucchini and salt.
Let stand and drain for 15 minutes, squeezing out excess liquid with back of spoon.

title: chile-egg puff
directions: Shred Jack cheese.
Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add cottage cheese and margarine.
Mix well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt and mix.
Add shredded cheese and chiles and stir to blend.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes or until edges are lightly browned and center appears firm.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Beat the first 7 ingredients and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle the nuts, chocolate chips and marshmallows on top.
Then beat egg whites stiff.
Add brown sugar.
Spread over bars.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cheesy-bacon potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes and onion in small pieces, about the size you would use for hash browns or fried potatoes.
Cover with enough water in a Dutch oven pan to boil them good.
When potatoes and onion are tender, don't drain off the water.
I add enough milk to fill the kettle about half to 2/3 full.
Then add your cheese, cut up in small chunks, bacon bits, seasonings and butter.
Let simmer until cheese melts and is good and hot.
It is a quick and easy meal for a cold evening and adds a zest to just plain potato soup.

title: veggie squares
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and salad dressing; set aside. Unroll crescent rolls and flatten on cookie sheet.
Bake 7 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
When cool, spread with cream cheese mixture.
Top with vegetables (carrots, radishes, broccoli, cauliflower, green pepper and mushrooms).
Add tomatoes, then Cheddar cheese.
Press down lightly.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares and serve as appetizer.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream margarine with sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time; add Ricotta and vanilla last.
Beat in flour a little at a time.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: texas corn chowder
directions: In medium saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour. Add potatoes, water and bouillon. Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 7 to 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add corn, jalapeno, milk and seasonings. Cover and simmer 15 minutes. This recipe only serves 2. Double if you want more.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Bring to boil first 4 ingredients.
Sift together sugar, flour and salt.
Add eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and soda.
Pour boiled mix into flour mixture and beat well.
Add eggs and milk mixture and beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 23 minutes.
(Do not overcook.)
Remove from oven and spread peanut butter on cake while hot.
Top with Easiest Chocolate Icing.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Place margarine in 9 x 13 baking dish and place dish in oven to melt margarine. Beat together 1 cup sugar, self-rising flour and milk to a smooth batter. Pour over melted butter and do not stir. Empty a can of fruit over batter and sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar over top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Batter will rise to top.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain off drippings.
Spoon beef into 8-inch casserole dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese.

title: buttery dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in water; let stand 5 minutes.
Scald milk; stir in 1/4 cup butter, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add unbeaten eggs, yeast and flour.
Beat vigorously.
Cover and let rise in warm place (80° to 85°) about 1 hour.
Stir well and spoon into greased muffin pan cups, filling them about 1/2 full.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk (about 30 minutes).
Pour 1/2 teaspoon melted butter over each roll; bake in preheated moderate oven (375°) for 20 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: new orleans red beans
directions: Rinse and sort beans; set aside.
Heat heavy 5-quart pot (medium-high heat).
Add ham; sear rapidly to brown both sides. Remove from pot.
Add sausage.
Keep heat adjusted so bottom of pot forms brown crust, but does not burn.
Remove sausage when brown on all sides.
Remove fat except for small film over crust.
Add onions, celery, garlic and parsley.
Stir and scrape bottom of pot to break up coagulated particles.
When onions are soft and brown, add water, beans, meat, bay leaves, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat and simmer covered 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until beans are tender. Return to medium-high heat and boil uncovered rapidly for 5 minutes or until beans start to break up.
With back of spoon, smash some beans against sides of pot and stir to thicken gravy.
Adjust seasoning and serve over steamed rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: green sauce
directions: Place cottage cheese in blender or food processor and blend until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Thin with a small amount of low-fat milk, if necessary.
Makes about 1 cup, 1 serving equals 1/4 cup.

title: washday cabbage
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil; add hamburger and brown.
Add salt, pepper and any other seasoning you like.
Wedge cabbage; place over meat.
Pour tomato sauce over cabbage.
Fill with water and pour over meat.
Cover and simmer 30 to 35 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender; drain well.
Mash squash; add onion, eggs, sugar, salt, pepper and 1/2 butter.
Place in dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Melt remaining butter and spread over cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: german meat loaf
directions: Mix above ingredients together except ketchup.
Place in oblong loaf pan. Spread ketchup over top and sides of meat loaf. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/4 hours, uncovered.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough for 1 hour.
Slice into 1/8-inch slices. Spray a 14-inch round glass pizza pan with a nonstick spray. Completely cover the pan with cookie dough slices, overlapping the edges slightly.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Combine milk, crumbs and eggs.
Pour in a well buttered dish.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: gueogan bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; set aside.
In mixing bowl add hot coffee to butter, sugar and syrup, then add dry ingredients and mix only until mixture is turned well.
Bake in well-greased and heated cast-iron skillets (two 8-inch) at 325° about 25 minutes or until bread springs back to touch.
Turn immediately to cake plate and butter bottom layer and add top layer.

title: icebox fruitcake
directions: Melt marshmallows with butter. Soften raisins in hot water and drain.
Mix rest of ingredients and mix well. Form into
pan and keep refrigerated.
Makes about 4 small fruitcake pans.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put the peaches in the bottom of the pan. Mix sugar and flour together and place over peaches (dry). Add melted butter over top. Cook for 30 minutes at 350° or 400° until brown.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and combine all other ingredients.
Pour in baking dish.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes, then top with buttered bread crumbs, seasoned with Lawry's garlic salt. Brown for about 10 minutes.

title: blackberry or dewberry puddin
directions: Work sugar and butter (or margarine) together.
Put in flour with baking powder, salt and milk.
Stir good.
Pour berries on top, then 1 cup sugar and 2 cups water.
Bake an hour.

title: apple coleslaw
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss well and set aside.
Combine next 7 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Toss gently.
Cover and chill 8 hours. Serve with a slotted spoon.
Yields 16 servings.
Contains about 54 calories and 1.8 grams of fat per 1/2-cup serving.

title: peanut butter oatmeal muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Oil enough cups in muffin tins for 12 muffins or line the cups with paper baking cups.

title: rice casserole
directions: Add ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into a greased 10 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir once about halfway, adding water, if too dry.
Yields 8 servings.

title: overnight french toast
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put two layers of bread on top.
Mix eggs with milk and pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Flip slices over to serve.
There will be a caramel-like glaze, which is very good, on top.
No need for butter or syrup on this French toast!

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Rinse dill juice from pickles and then soak pickles in ice water for at least 2 hours. Drain. Bring the sugar, vinegar and 1 cup of water to a boil in a large pan. Add the pickles and bring to a boil again. Cool. Store in refrigerator. Best if stored for a couple of days before eating.

title: chinese-style pepper steak
directions: Partially freeze steak, then slice across the grain into 3 x 1/8-inch strips.
Brown meat in hot oil in a large skillet; add next 7 ingredients.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a lightly greased 3 1/2 qt. slow cooker.
Cover and cook on high for 30 minutes or until cheese melts; stir occasionally.
Cover and continue to cook on high until smooth and cheese is melted.
Add more milk if needed; turn to low for 3 to 4 hours.
Just before serving, remove cover. Makes about 1 qt.

title: cherry freeze
directions: Mix all the ingredients together. Place in bowl with sealable lid. Place in freezer 1 to 2 hours or until ready to serve.
Will last approximately 2 weeks in freezer if properly stored.

title: peanut butter and jam bars
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in flour, soda and powder.
Reserve one cup (scant) dough.
Press remaining dough into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with jam.
Crumble remaining dough over jam.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and drizzle with glaze.

title: joe's dill pickles
directions: Simmer sugar, salt, vinegar and water together; cool.
Wash and dry enough cukes to fill a gallon jar.
Arrange with layers of cukes, dill, garlic and hot peppers until jar is full.
Pour cooled juice over and refrigerate.
Good to eat in about 1 week.

title: creamy holiday fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and stir in condensed milk, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Spread mixture evenly into an 8 x 8-inch pan, lined with wax paper.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board and peel off wax paper.
Cut into squares. Tightly cover.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and add Ragu sauce.
Simmer while mixing remaining ingredients.
Boil lasagna noodles for 10 minutes. Drain and rinse in cold water.
Grate Mozzarella cheese.
Set aside.
Mix together cottage cheese, eggs, parsley, Parmesan cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Place one layer of
noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with half of the cottage cheese mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 the grated Mozzarella cheese on top. Spread 1/2 the hamburger/Ragu on top.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand about 10 minutes after removing from oven before slicing into servings.
May be wrapped in aluminum foil and frozen.

title: caramel corn puffs
directions: Place corn and nuts in a large kettle.
Combine butter, sugar and syrup in a 4-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and pour in soda and vanilla.
Pour over corn, stirring to mix and coat.
Bake in a 250° oven for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Let cool and store in covered container.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Cut up chicken and put in crock-pot; add onions, peppers and celery.
Make a dark brown gravy (enough to cover ingredients in crock-pot).
Pour gravy over all ingredients and cook in covered crock-pot until chicken is done.
Serve over rice.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, add oil, sugar, some flour or all, apples and vanilla.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Punch holes in hot cake.
Pour over topping.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well and make a well in the middle.
Mix rest of ingredients, then pour all at once into well. Beat well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes in 2 large loaf pans.

title: banana cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water, oil and bananas and blend to moisten at medium speed, about 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts. Pour into tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: baked ziti
directions: In saucepan prepare ziti as directed.
In nonstick skillet, saute in olive oil the green pepper, onion and celery.
Slowly add tomato puree, tomato sauce and tomato paste to skillet.
Add oregano, basil and garlic to tomato mixture.
Heat to boiling. Remove from heat.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, evaporated milk and oleo in a 3 to 4-quart microwave-safe dish.
Cook on High for 22 minutes, stirring every 5 minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well until chocolate chips are melted.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate and cut into pieces.
Make 5 pounds of candy.

title: waffles
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk, baking powder, salt, sugar and flour.
Beat well.
Add shortening.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Cook on hot waffle iron.

title: deviled cream cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Serve with crackers or stuff celery.

title: pat's noodles
directions: Melt butter in large skillet. Add noodles and onion. Stir over low heat until mixture begins to brown, then add green pepper, salt and pepper. When browned, place in 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Prepare rice according to package directions. Add to mixture in baking dish and mix together. Pour chicken broth over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Rinse sauerkraut under running cold water.
Drain well.
Dice red and green pepper.

title: scottish mince
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan. Add onions and carrots and fry gently until soft and pale gold. Add hamburger meat and fry until well-browned. Stir in oatmeal and tomato paste, then gradually blend in stock. Season to taste with salt and pepper and bring to boil, stirring. Lower heat; cover pan. Simmer for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve hot with mashed potatoes and vegetables.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Cut shortening into biscuit mix until crumbly.
Combine 3 tablespoons of sugar, vanilla and milk.
Stir into biscuit mix. Beat 15 strokes.
Pat into 2 well-greased 8-inch cake pans.
Bake in hot oven (400°)
for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.

title: barbecued brisket
directions: Combine seasonings and rub into brisket.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce and liquid smoke.
Place fat side up in roaster and bake, covered, at 250° for 5 hours or 200° for 8 hours.
Place on cookie sheet; cover with your favorite barbecue sauce.
Return to oven and bake, covered, 1 hour longer.
Cool, then slice thinly with electric knife.
Can be prepared a day ahead, then reheat, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
If preparing ahead, wait until day of serving to slice.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken, remove from bone and cut into small pieces. Save broth.
Saute green pepper and onion in butter; add soups, chicken and tomatoes.
Heat.
Grease casserole and completely line with Doritos that have been softened in chicken broth.
Cover with chicken mixture and top with grated cheese.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 good size casseroles.
Freeze one for later.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Beat all ingredients except nuts in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl frequently, 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 3 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely before slicing. Refrigerate any remaining bread.

title: beef stew
directions: Melt shortening in a large pot over medium to medium-high heat.
Add beef and brown lightly, stirring frequently.
Lower heat to medium-low.
Add beef broth and tomato juice (should equal 2 cups).
Add 1/2 cup water.
Add all spices.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour on medium-low.
Add all vegetables and simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours until vegetables are tender.
Just before serving, you may thicken with a mixture of 3 tablespoons flour and 1/2 to 1/3 cup water.
Shake in covered cup and add slowly to stew, stirring constantly.

title: squash dressing
directions: Saute onion in oleo, then mix well with all other ingredients. You may want to save some of the liquid from the squash and add to mixture if seems to be dry.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: mexican fudge pie
directions: Mix cocoa, flour and sugar together.
Add margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
Can top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: ronald's corn casserole
directions: Heat together cooked rice, the soups (do not add water) and corn.
Add butter, onion and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish. Top with slices of sandwich cheese. Bake in preheated oven at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until cheese is browned.

title: coconut pineapple pie
directions: Combine all filling ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix together eggs, oil and orange juice.
Add 2 cups of sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour half of the dough mixture into the pan. Mix together the apples, 1/2 cup sugar* and cinnamon.
Put half the apple mixture on the dough.
Cover with the remaining dough mixture and follow with the remaining apple mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Add butter and cream cheese to spinach.
Stir and blend together.
Put in bowl and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Beat eggs; stir in milk and oil.
Add flour only until moist. Add berries.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Fill cups 2/3 full.

title: great pecan cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and shortening and add dry ingredients and milk alternately.
Beat with an electric beater.
Add pecans. Bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for one hour.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over apples to prevent discoloring.
Toss with yogurt and refrigerate.

title: olive stuffed celery
directions: Cut olives in small pieces to measure 1/2 cup.
Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise or sour cream.
Add onion, chives or parsley and olives.
Season with salt.
Fill celery stalks; cut into pieces about 2 inches in length.
Chill and serve.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Cut in shortening, 1/2 at a time.
Sprinkle over this mixture 5 tablespoons of water.
Mix with fork.
Round into a ball and let stand a few minutes.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into 7 squares.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with low-fat cooking oil.
Place hash browns in bottom of baking dish. Mix sour cream, milk, soup and margarine together and pour over hash browns.
Grate cheese on top.
Top it all with crushed potato chips.
Bake 1 hour covered with foil and 15 to 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: biscuits
directions: Use Pastry Blender to cut dry ingredients into shortening, and add milk.
Knead and roll out on floured board.
Cut about an inch high-width as desired.
Bake at 450 degrees for about 10 - 12 minutes.

title: "veggie" casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers, well.
Put into a casserole dish and top with crushed Ritz crackers or Cheez-Its. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Wash, hull and crush strawberries.
Whip the cream until thickened.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly.
Add salt and beat until cream is stiff.
Fold in strawberries and almonds.
Turn into 2-quart mold.
Freeze until firm.
Unmold onto serving plate. Garnish with whole strawberries and mint sprigs, if desired. Serves 6 to 8.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spiced tea
directions: Makes
a little over a quart when mixed together.
Seal in container
for
later use.
Add as much as desired to taste and stir in boiling water.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Cover rhubarb with sugar and let set 2 hours or until sugar dissolves.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in Jell-O. Pour into jars, let cool and freeze.
Keep in refrigerator after opening.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Add bananas.
Pour half of jello mixture in 11 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Chill until firm.
Spoon sour cream over chilled mixture.
Top with remaining gelatin.
May be garnished with fresh strawberries if desired. Refrigerate until served.

title: cranberry orange salad
directions: Put gelatin in a medium bowl. Pour in water and stir constantly until gelatin has dissolved. Stir in orange juice. Cover and refrigerate until almost jellied, about 30 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients except vegetable oil spray, stirring well. Fold into gelatin
mixture. Spray a 1-quart mold with vegetable oil spray. Pour mixture into mold. Cover and refrigerate until firm, about 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape firmly into a loaf.
Bake in shallow pan at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: bachelor buttons
directions: Mix together all ingredients except brown sugar.
Form into balls.
Roll in brown sugar.
Press with walnuts or pecans and candied cherries.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown beef along with mushrooms and drain grease.
Add seasoning mix, water as directed on package and tomato paste.
Mix well. Set aside.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat until lemon color.
Add shortening.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add cream mixture.
Alternate with milk and stir in flavors.
Spoon mixture into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, or until cake tests done.

title: apricot squares
directions: Cut margarine into flour and cake mix with a fork.
Add chopped pecans and coconut.
Mix well.
Pat 3/4 of mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan and press firmly.
Spread apricot preserves over crust.
Crumble remainder of mix on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until golden brown.
May use different types of preserves, if desired.

title: skillet casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Stir in other ingredients and simmer, stirring occasionally 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Moisten oats with apple juice.
Pat onto the bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: In large bowl, toss together spaghetti, egg substitute, margarine, Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes; set aside.

title: black chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in milk.
Set aside to cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Add chocolate and milk mixture.
Mix well. Add dry ingredients, sifted together, and vanilla.
Bake in greased square cake pan at 375° for 30 minutes.
Batter is very thin.
If lumpy, put through sieve.
Delicious, moist and inexpensive.

title: frothy orange shake
directions: In blender in 2 batches, place milk, frozen orange juice and frozen vanilla yogurt.
Process until smooth and frothy.
Pour into 3-quart pitcher.
Stir in cold water.

title: almond hershey marshmallow pie
directions: In a double boiler, melt the Hershey bars, marshmallows and milk. Allow to cool. Whip 1 cup of whipping cream and blend with the chocolate mixture. Put into a regular crust or graham cracker crust.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Beat sugar and eggs, then unsalted butter.
Add sour cream, water and vanilla; beat.
Add (sift twice) flour, baking soda and double-acting baking soda.
Add cocoa.
Beat, just until flour is absorbed.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into buttered Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, sift powdered sugar on top.

title: white mountain icing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let boil until it will form a ball in water.
Beat the whites of three eggs, then mix with syrup and beat with mixer until real stiff.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: In large bowl, sift together sugar and flour. In saucepan, bring margarine, cocoa and water to a boil.
Pour over flour-sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, soda, eggs and cinnamon.
Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.
Make icing 5 minutes before cake is done.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Combine graham crackers, saltine crackers and margarine. Spread 2/3 mixture in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix pudding and milk.
Blend ice cream into pudding and pour over crumbs. Refrigerate until firm.
Spread Cool Whip on firm cake.
Crush Butterfingers and combine with remaining crackers and sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.

title: aunt nora's pineapple upside down cake
directions: Pour batter over this and bake.

title: maize-ing cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, mix corn, brown sugar and sugar.
Beat eggs, one at a time.
Add oil and beat well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add all liquids at once and stir until well blended.
Pour into 9-inch pans or 9 x 15-inch dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until tests done. If desired, frost with caramel frosting.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Cut the first 3 ingredients up like pie dough. Reserve 1 cup for topping. Add the remaining ingredients. Blend well. Pour into an 8 x 12 greased and floured pan. Sprinkle the top of cake with the crumb topping. Crush 6 Heath bars and sprinkle over the top of the crumb topping. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put into dish that can go into oven.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cucumber spread
directions: Place cucumber and onion on paper towels and squeeze out moisture.
Beat cream cheese until smooth and stir in vegetables, salad dressing and salt.
Add lemon juice.
Serve spread with fresh vegetables or crackers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Bring sugar, white syrup and vanilla to boil.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter until smooth, then add corn flakes. Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: cran-rasp-apple jello
directions: Combine all and chill.
Great with pork and chicken.

title: egg casserole
directions: Place cubed bread in baking dish.
Brown meat in skillet and drain.
Spoon meat over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pickled herring
directions: Squeeze the lemons.
Make a marinade of lemon juice, water, sugar and seasonings.
Simmer the marinade (it must not boil).
Let it cool.
Drain the herring fillets well.
Cut them into pieces and chop the onion and leek.
Put the herring and the chopped onion, leek and dill into a glass jar in layers.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix in and blend 1 1/2 sticks butter. Pack in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs and 1 stick butter.
Blend 5 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Slice bananas; press in sugar mixture.
Add drained pineapple, then Cool Whip, then chopped nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: beef hash
directions: Melt butter and add remaining ingredients.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Brown hash. Add onion to your taste.

title: honey raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt together.
Beat egg, shortening and honey in bowl.
Stir in flour mixture alternately with milk and buttermilk just until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in raisins and pecans.
Spoon into pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until it tests done.
If browning too fast, cover with foil.
Remove bread from pan to rack and slice when thoroughly cool.
May be frozen.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together by hand, roll into bite size balls. Freeze until needed.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown. Yields 100.

title: unbaked fudge cookies
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 3 minutes (exactly).
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, salt and oats.
Stir in vanilla. Drop on wax paper to cool.

title: beth's vegetable spaghetti pie
directions: Place spaghetti in bottom of a 9-inch pie pan.
Pour melted butter over top.
Put in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
When you make standard recipe cream medium sauce, substitute coleslaw seasoning for salt.
Add cooked vegetables to sauce and optional meat.
Stir together and pour into pie shell.
Heat at 350° an additional 15 minutes or so.
May top with grated cheese if you wish.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs and soup mix.
Form meat balls and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: healthy cookies
directions: Mix in order given.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten a little and bake at 350° for 9 minutes.

title: 16 minute chop suey
directions: In Dutch oven, place margarine or oil and onion.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add celery, salt and hot water.
Cook 5 minutes in the oil.
Add bean sprouts and cooked meat.
Cook 5 minutes.
Combine cold water, cornstarch, soy sauce and sugar and add the first mixture.
Cook 1 minute.
Serve on hot cooked rice.

title: fettucini with vegetables
directions: Saute onions and garlic in olive oil until onions are translucent, not brown.
Add pretty, green broccoli.
Add Green Giant corn niblets.
Add fresh spinach fettucini that has been cooked.
Stir until ingredients are blended and warm.
Add 1/2 cup white cooking wine.
Stir and cook 2 or 3 minutes.
Do not cook too long or vegetables will be mushy.
Place on warm platter.
Add bacon bits and serve.

title: chile verde con carne
directions: Brown meat lightly in hot oil and salt to taste.
Add onions; cook until clear.
Add tomatoes and water to cover.
Add garlic and chilies.
(Two diced potatoes may be added if heartier dish is desired.)
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: peanut butter round-up cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and peanut butter, beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture, mix well.
Stir in oatmeal.
Shape into 1-inch balls, place onto ungreased cookie sheet and press crisscross with a fork.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix muffin mix according to directions.
Add other ingredients.
Pour mixture into greased pan or muffin pan and bake in oven preheated to 375° for 25 minutes or until done.
Test with toothpick by sticking it in center of bread.
Serves approximately 8.

title: nanimo bars
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and cook on top of stove 1 minute. Mix and add the following 3 ingredients.
Press into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix and add the next 4 ingredients.
Spread on top of first mixture.
Melt semi-sweet chocolate with butter.

title: corn muffins
directions: Combine the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine the liquid ingredients in another bowl.
Add the liquid ingredients to the dry ingredients.
Add the corn.
Stir just until blended. Spoon batter into paper lined muffin cups.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: banana cherry nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 325 degrees for 50-60 minutes.

title: streusel
directions: Mix together first three ingredients until crumbly.
Pat half of mixture onto a greased jelly roll pan.
Spread filling over crust.
Sprinkle the rest of the mixture over top of filling. Bake for 45 minutes on 350
degrees.

title: rice with ham, peas and cheese(takes thirty minutes to prepare)
directions: Cut ham into squares, about 3/4-inch.
Set aside.
Heat butter in heavy lidded casserole.
Add onion and saute for 2 minutes until tender.
Stir in the rice.
Mix until rice is evenly coated with butter.
Add the frozen peas and ham, then add the broth. Bring to boiling.
Stir once.
Cover and turn heat down to low. Cook for 20 minutes.
