Rice should absorb all the liquid in this time.
Fold in the Parmesan cheese.
Add butter, if desired taste. Add salt and pepper.

title: six can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (all soups undiluted) in a casserole; sprinkle top with dry cereal (any kind will do, but corn flakes are best).
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 375°, then uncover for 15 minutes more.

title: baked fish
directions: Place fish fillets on a microwavable dish.
Top with pats of margarine and onion.
Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Turn fish over and microwave 3 minutes on High.
Ready to serve.

title: razzle-dazzle raspberry shake
directions: In blender container, blend apricot nectar, lemonade and ice cream until smooth.
Add berries and ice cubes; blend again.

title: seven week bran muffins
directions: Mix
together both the brans and the boiling water; let stand. Mix
together
the eggs, butter, sugar and buttermilk. Add
to the
bran
mixture.
Sift
the flour, baking soda and salt.
Fold the dry ingredients into the bran mixture and stir until combined.
Fill
muffin
pans
3/4 full and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lipton extra special spinach dip
directions: In a medium bowl, blend soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Stir in thawed and squeezed dry spinach and water chestnuts.
Chill.
Serve with Ritz crackers.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: stovers fudge
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, milk, butter and salt.
Cook 10 minutes after coming to a boil.
In a bowl, mix chocolate, bits and marshmallow cream.
Pour the hot mixture over the bowl mixture and beat until all the chocolate is melted and well blended.
Add nuts last and pour into a buttered pan.

title: chewy pecan squares
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in greased and floured pan at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate nut clusters
directions: Lightly oil two baking sheets.
In a heavy bottomed saucepan over medium heat, cook the first six ingredients until the sugars dissolve and the butter melts.
Bring to a boil and cook, stirring frequently, for about 1 hour, until the caramel reaches 238°F (soft ball stage) on a candy thermometer.

title: "free" vegetable soup
directions: Vary amounts of each vegetable to suit your own taste.
Put all in a soup pot.
Season with herbs to taste.
Simmer until vegetables are just slightly crisp, not soft.
This is very low in fat and calories so you can eat all you want.

title: one of life's recipes
directions: Mix these thoroughly.
Add tears of joy and sorrow and sympathy for others.
Fold in 4 cup prayers, a faith to lighten other ingredients and raise the texture to great heights of Christian living.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spray loaf pan with Pam.
Pack ingredients in pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey and hash brown casserole
directions: Brown turkey with onions and garlic.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased (or spray with Pam) 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: spice cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter together until fluffy.
Add eggs and beat until light.
Sift together all dry ingredients, then add them alternately with the milk to the creamed mixture, beating well after each addition, then mix in the vanilla.
Pour into greased layer pans or a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: copy pop
directions: In 2 1/2-quart mixing bowl, combine butter, syrup and sugar. Microwave at High 9 to 15 minutes, or until brittle threads form when small amount is dropped in cold water, stirring every 3 minutes.

title: vegetarian black bean chili
directions: Saute onion and peppers in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Add black beans, tomatoes, water and spices.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add carrots and mushrooms and any other vegies you like and continue simmering until vegies are tender.

title: potato-leek soup
directions: About 45 minutes before using, cut off roots and discard tough leaves from leeks. Cut each leek lengthwise in half.
Rinse with running cold water to remove sand.
Cut white part of leeks and enough green tips crosswise into 1/4-inch slices (2 cups).
Heat leeks, potatoes and carrots in broth.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and cook 25 minutes.
Add milk.
Serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing mix including flavor package with 1 stick of butter.
Spread 3/4 of mixture on bottom of pan.
Layer in the following order:
chicken and mushrooms.
Combine sour cream, chicken soup and 1 cup broth.
Pour over layers.
Sprinkle rest of stuffing mixture on top.
Pour remaining chicken broth (1/2 cup) on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: appleberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and add strawberries.
Stir until berries are thawed.
Add applesauce and chill until firm. Serve on lettuce with sour cream, if desired.
Serves 8.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Fold into batter 1/3 cup evaporated milk, melted margarine and chopped nuts.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
While baking first half, melt the caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in top of double boiler.
Pour this mixture over baked first half.
Sprinkle chips over caramel mixture.
Cover with remaining cake batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or longer, if needed.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Place shredded cabbage in large mixing bowl and spread chopped peppers and onion over top; add salt, pepper and Accent.
Do not stir.
Mix oil, sugar and vinegar in saucepan and bring to full boil; pour over cabbage mixture and let stand at room temperature for one hour.
Mix well and refrigerate; keeps indefinitely.

title: better than pudding
directions: Combine flour, butter and nuts in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar together with 10 ounces Cool Whip (mixture will thicken).
Mix milk and pudding; beat for 2 minutes.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix well and add milk. Add soda and baking powder to flour and mix well.
Add to creamed mixture along with dates, nuts and candied cherries. Chill.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: jambalojia
directions: Saute onion, celery, green pepper and mushrooms in butter in large skillet until tender about 5 minutes.
Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in water.
Add 57 sauce.
Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Add ham, chicken and shrimp.
Also add tomatoes. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Layer bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with vanilla wafers and sliced bananas.
Pour half of pudding mixture on top and repeat layers.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients in pan to be used.
Make three holes in dry mixture.
In first hole, put vinegar.
In second, put oleo. In third, put vanilla.
Pour water over mixture.
Stir with fork until well mixed.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Barely cover the potatoes, onion and celery with water and boil about 20 minutes.
Skim off most water, but don't drain.
Add half and half and butter.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Cover and let set.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 250° until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bacon cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate at least overnight. Form into 2 balls. May roll in almonds or pecans if desired. Serve with crackers of choice.

title: better than robert redford dessert
directions: Melt margarine; add flour and nuts.
Spread and pat down in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes (until slightly brown).
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip together.
Spread carefully on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk; blend for 2 minutes, until smooth.
Spread over cheese mixture.
Top with 8 to 9 ounces Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.

title: homemade butterfinger ice cream
directions: Make sure candy bars are frozen.
Crush candy bars.
Mix together chocolate milk, condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Add crushed candy bars; mix well.
Place in ice cream churn and freeze.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together all ingredients except flour.
Gradually add flour, mixing well.
Drop by spoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: rolls
directions: Sift self-rising flour into a wooden bread tray.
Fill to almost full (about 5 cups).
Make a doodle-hole in the middle of the flour.
Add 1 tablespoon of sugar and 2 packages dry yeast. Add shortening.
Heat milk to lukewarm.
Work it in by hand. After working dough well, place it in a warm place until double in size (about 1 hour).
Punch down.
Make rolls out to desired size. Let these set 1 hour.
Bake at 450° until golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Butter while hot.

title: squash casserole #6
directions: Boil
squash
until
tender.
Mix
first 5 ingredients. Melt butter
and mix with stuffing.
Line casserole dish with stuffing. Reserve
1/3 for top.
Pour casserole mix into dish and top with remainder of stuffing.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bean spice cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, mashed potatoes, cocoa and flour, alternately with the milk.
Add raisins, nutmeats and spices. Bake in layer pans or in a loaf pan.
Frost with vanilla frosting.

title: vegetarian pizza 2
directions: Place crescent rolls flat on an ungreased cookie sheet to form the dough.
Bake as directed.
Cool.

title: cherry chowder
directions: In a large saucepan saute garlic, onion and mushrooms in the butter over low heat or until onions are soft.
Slowly stir in half and half and chicken broth, cook.
Continue stirring until slightly thick and smooth.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Gradually add grated cheese, stir until melted.
Add ham, Worcestershire, broccoli, carrots, corn and pepper.
Heat chowder over moderately low heat.
Do not boil.
Serve immediately.

title: quick spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in large microwave-safe dish with a lid.
Cook on High for 10 to 12 minutes or until firm. Makes 10 servings.

title: corny bean dip
directions: Mix the three ingredients together.
Store in a covered container and keep refrigerated.
Serve with Fritos - scoop variety.
This is just simple but most delightful to snack on with family or friends. Yield: 2 1/2 cups.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Beat egg
whites
stiff.
Add sugar a little at a time. Add pecans
and
baking powder.
Crumble crackers fine and add to mixture.
Pour into a buttered pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30	minutes.
Cool.
Top
with Dream Whip (according to directions on
box).	Add
chocolate.

title: cool lemon pie
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk and lemonade concentrate; fold in whipped topping.
Pour mixture into crust.
Cover and freeze for 8 hours or overnight.
Cut pie into slices; place on individual serving plates.
Garnish with lemon slices, if desired. Serves 10.

title: pull-apart bread(monkey bread)
directions: In a saucepan, combine 1 cup of sugar, oleo, vanilla and fruit juice.
Boil for 1 minute; set aside.
Open biscuits and cut each into quarters.
Combine 1/2 cup of sugar and cinnamon into a shaker bag.
Place quartered biscuits, a few at a time, in shaker bag to coat with sugar mixture.
Remove and layer into a well-greased Bundt pan.
Pour about 1/3 of the boiled mixture over biscuits.
Repeat with another layer of sugar coated biscuit pieces and pour liquid mixture on top.
Keep repeating until all ingredients are used up and Bundt pan is full to top edge.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Turn bread out of pan as soon as it comes out of the oven. Cool.
Use fingers to pull apart and enjoy.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In a small bowl, combine lime juice, garlic, chili powder and cumin.
Add chicken; stir.
Marinate for 15 minutes.
In a nonstick skillet, cook onion, chicken and marinate for 3 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Add peppers; saute for 3 to 5 minutes or until crisp.
Stir in salsa.
Divide mixture among tortillas and top with cheese.
Roll up and serve.
Serve with sour cream.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: homemade copier
directions: Dissolve gelatine (as much as possible) in water.
In well ventilated area, put anti-freeze in top of double boiler and stir in dissolved gelatine.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes, stirring until gelatine is dissolved, then heat until well heated and well mixed. Pour into disposable aluminum jelly roll pan and let set for 24 hours at room temperature.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Combine soup, milk, pepper and salt.
Heat thoroughly, but do not bring to a boil.
Set aside.
Place a layer of sliced potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart ungreased casserole.
Add a layer of ham, then a layer of onion slices.
Repeat until all have been used.
Pour soup mixture over all.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover, sprinkle shredded cheese on top, and add a dash of paprika.
Bake an additional 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix all together.
Add chile if you like it hot.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: john's 3 bean bake
directions: Cut wieners in small round pieces.
Add all the beans together. Stir.
Add sugar and onions.
Stir.
Add wieners.
Place in microwave.
Cook 5 minutes on High.
Stop, stir.
Cook on Low for 10 minutes.
Stop.
Stir.
Low again for 10 more minutes.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Mix cracker crumbs and powdered sugar in a large mixing bowl; mix well.
Melt butter with peanut butter and add to the first mixture.
Mix well.
Press very firmly into a well buttered 13 x 9-inch cake pan.

title: green chili
directions: Put in crock-pot and cook all day on low or simmer in dutch oven until done.
I thicken it with cornstarch and water mixture to the consistency I like.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Place all ingredients in cake pan in order given.
Bake at 300° for about 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Cook rice; follow directions on box.
Saute onion until soft; stir flour into onion.
Add soup and chicken broth.
Can add 1/2 can water to thin, if necessary.

title: sandy o's guacamole dip
directions: *I use Herbamare from the health food store.

title: italian cheese straws
directions: Combine cheese and butter, stirring until blended.
Gradually add remaining ingredients, stirring until mixture is no longer crumbly and will shape into a ball.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cook bacon.
Put small chopped onion in drippings and simmer until onion is shiny.
Shred cabbage, add tomatoes and cut up all other ingredients.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours until everything cooks down.
Great at Thanksgiving.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Peel and cut eggplant into 1/4-inch slices.
Brown in oil and drain.
Layer eggplant, 1/2 of the oregano, 1/2 of the salt, 1/2 of the Mozzarella, 1/2 of the tomato puree, 1/4 cup water and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread and cool. Crumble in a large bowl. Add all other ingredients and chill. Note: Do not cover airtight.

title: individual meat loaves
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into balls, about the size of small orange.
(I use glass cake pan.)
Wrap each ball with 1/2 strip bacon.

title: baked fruit salad
directions: Melt butter; remove from heat.
Add brown sugar and dry mustard and stir until mixed.
Put fruit and juices in casserole dish and mix in mixture.
Add grapes, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients into a long greased pan.
Blend oleo and flour; add milk.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: fried rice
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet, add eggs, cook over medium heat until almost set.
Stir in onions, peppers and rice.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently; add soy sauce.
Cook 2 minutes. Stir in peanuts.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients (mixture will be soft) and shape into walnut size balls.
Place meatballs in a single layer in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with following sauce.

title: crunchy punch
directions: Freeze together in container.
When ready to use, thaw.
Mix with 1 bottle ginger ale.
Serves about 20.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 to 8.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Boil for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoon on waxed paper.

title: calico beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, cook bacon for 1 minute.
Add beef and onion and cook, stirring with fork to break up meat, until the beef is browned.
Drain off grease.
Add ketchup, sugar, brown sugar, dry mustard, salt and vinegar, stirring and blending.
Spoon the mixture into a 3-quart casserole dish and add remaining ingredients, stirring lightly to blend. Bake 1 hour and serve hot.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in refrigerator to marinate so flavors wil blend.
Very good.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut in colander for 15 minutes, cut into pieces with kitchen scissors.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well.
Store covered in refrigerator for at least 2 hours.
Keeps indefinitely.
Serves 10.

title: unleavened communion bread
directions: Work butter in with flour and add honey and milk.
Roll dough very thin on wax paper and place paper with dough on cookie sheet. Mark with knife in tiny squares.
Paper will not burn when in oven nor bread brown as it is baked in slow heat about 200°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Make the crust from the first 2 ingredients, mixing the butter in cracker crumbs.
Beat the next 3 ingredients on high speed until fluffy.
Spread on crust.
Split the bananas lengthwise. Put them in next, then put pineapple on.
Add Cool Whip on top of pineapple.
Put cherry pie filling on top and refrigerate.

title: good ole kabobs
directions: Add all ingredients in gallon container and let stand for 12 to 24 hours. Do not refrigerate.
Put meat on skewer and barbecue.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, biscuit mix, egg, butter and milk.
Mix well. Turn one half the butter into a well greased 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with chiles, then cheese slices.
Spread remaining dough over cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until browned.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 to 9 servings.

title: grilled asparagus
directions: Crush garlic. Mix with olive oil in small bowl. Add salt and pepper; set aside.

title: puffed potato pancakes
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine potatoes, eggs, onion and celery. Mix together flour, baking powder and salt. Stir into potato mixture and add milk; blend well.

title: maryland fried chicken
directions: Combine eggs and 1/4 cup of the milk.
Mix cracker crumbs, salt and dash of pepper.
Dip legs into egg mixture, then roll in crumbs.
In heavy skillet, brown chicken in hot shortening.
Turn with tongs.
Add remaining 1 cup milk.
Cover tightly and simmer 35 minutes.
Uncover and cook about 10 minutes or until tender.

title: buttermilk drop biscuits
directions: Measure
flour
into
bowl, add baking powder, soda and salt. Stir
to
blend.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender or
fork until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk, stir
until ingredients are well moistened with fork.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: pecan delight pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into a large, greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: christy's favorite potato soup
directions: Wash, pare and slice potatoes. Cook with onion in the water just to cover potatoes in a covered saucepan for 15 minutes. Drain, keeping 1 1/2 cups of the water.
Mash the vegetables with a potato masher. Add butter, cooking water, evaporated milk and salt. Heat.
Add more water if a thinner soup is desired.
Add 1 teaspoon minced parsley to each serving.

title: sweet and sour macaroni
directions: Cook shells according to package directions and cool.
Boil sugar and vinegar; let cool.
When mixture is cool, add salad oil and tomato soup; mix well.
Pour over shells.
Add onion, pepper, celery, pimentos and carrot.
Chill.

title: mr. kerr's goulash
directions: Into a heavy pot that has a cover available, put the butter. Put pot and butter on heat until butter melted.
Add the onions, marjoram, salt, pepper and paprika; heat and stir until onions are translucent.
Add the flour and stir and cook for at least 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir until mix is cooled down a bit. Add the stock a bit at a time while stirring over heat.
Add tomato paste and vinegar; stir over heat.
Heat and stir until simmering.
Cover and low simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, or preheat oven to 325° and bake for same time but stir from time to time.
Serve over hot, buttered noodles with peas, etc.

title: confectioners sugar frosting
directions: Mix egg white and 1 cup confectioners sugar well.
Add another cup of confectioners sugar, flour, butter, Crisco, vanilla and milk.
Beat well until stiff.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately, starting with flour, then buttermilk, ending with flour.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: puget sound crab cakes
directions: Clean crabmeat of shells or cartilage, sprinkle with lemon juice and set aside.
Melt butter in heavy skillet over medium heat, adding flour, then milk, stirring until thickens.
Slowly stir hot sauce into beaten eggs.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in crabmeat; chill until firm.
Shape into 3-inch patties.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix and put in fridge. It is very good cold.

title: fresh mushroom soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter in a Dutch oven over medium heat until onion is tender.
Add mushrooms; cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until tender.
Gradually add cream, broth and sherry (optional).
Continue to cook until thoroughly heated.
Do not boil!

title: shrimp mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Cream the cream cheese and add with gelatin to heated soup.
Allow mixture to cool.
Add mayonnaise, celery, onions, bell pepper and seasonings.
Let stand in refrigerator until thickens, about 5 minutes.
Add shrimp. Place in well oiled mold.
Chill until firm (overnight).
Serve with crackers.

title: louisiana shrimp casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in a large casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cover top with cheese.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes, until cheese is browned.
Serves 6 to 8 or 4 people who are hungry!

title: raised pecan rolls
directions: Heat milk.
When lukewarm, add yeast and egg.
Add flour gradually; add sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Cut down and let rise again.
Place on floured board and roll as thinly as possible in a rectangular shape.
Spread with melted butter.
Sprinkle with plenty of brown sugar and chopped pecans.
Roll up carefully like jelly roll and slice in 1-inch pieces.
Place in greased muffin tins on the bottom of which has been sprinkled brown sugar and nuts.
Let rise half hour and then bake at 400° about 15 minutes.
Let rest one minute and invert on cookie sheet and cool on rack.

title: apple banana bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine eggs, mashed bananas, sugar, oil and milk.
In another large bowl, combine flour and wheat germ.
Add banana mixture to flour mixture.
Stir gently with wooden spoon until combined.
Fold apples into batter.
Pour batter into two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and enjoy.

title: breakfast doughnuts
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, shortening and sour milk until smooth.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, nutmeg and baking powder.
Add to mixture until doesn't stick to hands.
Let rise on floured board for about 20 minutes.
Roll and cut.
Deep fry at 390°, about 1 minute per side.

title: mama's seven layered salad
directions: You will need an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine ingredients and beat well.
Bake in greased layer cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crispy oven okra
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Trim off stem ends of okra and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Combine yellow cornmeal, salt and pepper in a medium bowl; stir mixture well and set aside. Combine buttermilk and egg in a large bowl; add okra, stirring to coat. Let stand 10 minutes. Drain an dredge okra in cornmeal mixture. Place okra on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Bake at 450° for 40 minutes or until crispy, stirring occasionally. Yield: 12 servings.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill and stir before serving.

title: chicken alfredo(low-fat)
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, blend flour, liquid Butter Buds, skim milk and chicken broth.
Add minced garlic, salt and pepper. Continue to cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Combine sauce with chicken and mushrooms.
Fold into cooked pasta.
Serve immediately.
Fat 3.83 grams per serving.
Serves 6.

title: amish date pudding
directions: Pour water over dates and soda.
Let stand until cool.
Add sugar, butter, flour, egg and nuts; mix well.
Bake like a cake on a greased 11 x 14-inch or larger pan in a 325° oven for about 35 minutes, or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean.
When cool, cut in 1-inch squares.
Alternate layers of cake, sliced bananas and whipped topping in a large bowl or individual containers.
Garnish with bananas.
Assemble near serving time, as bananas quickly discolor and soften.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix first five ingredients,
then add 3 medium mashed bananas, 1/2 cup nuts (optional).
Bake at 350° about an hour for large loaf pan.

title: alice's roast
directions: Mix water and all seasonings in large roaster and stir thoroughly.
Add meat.
Put roast in oven at 350° for 1 hour. Reduce heat to 300° and cook for about 3 hours.
Cool thoroughly. Slice thin and reheat in sauce before serving.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand until well dissolved.
Add sugar, shortening, potatoes, egg and salt.
Mix real good.
Add flour to make a fairly stiff dough.
Knead well. Cover and let rise in a warm place until almost double in size. Work out into small biscuits and place in greased pan (not too close).
Let rise until almost double in size.
Brush with butter and bake at 350°.

title: wild rice dish
directions: Melt butter.
Saute rice with seasonings until brown.
Chop and add other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 to 2 hours, covered.
Add extra water as needed.
Recipe can be halved.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Clean mushrooms, separating the caps and the stems.
Save the stems for another use.
Blend remaining ingredients and fill mushroom caps. Arrange in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pat's fantasy chili
directions: Season onion, garlic, peppers and hamburger.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 hour.

title: best cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and form in ball.
Mince pecans extra fine and roll ball in them.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Cream the butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour that has been sifted with baking powder and salt, alternating with milk.
Add lemon extract and pineapple.
Mix well.
Place in cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove cake and glaze while hot.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Combine ingredients in blender. Pulse 3 times in blender. Makes 1 pint.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix together and pour in pie shell. Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix ingredients.
May be stored in refrigerator up to 6 weeks. Fill muffin tins 2/3 full and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: spinach square
directions: Defrost spinach.
Squeeze spinach and dry on paper towels. Melt butter, sliced onions and mushrooms together.
In bowl, use 2 tablespoons of cheese and mix everything together.
Put in rectangular baking dish.
Sprinkle rest of Parmesan cheese on top and bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together the potatoes, egg yolks, 2 tablespoons butter, sugar, baking powder and orange juice or light cream.
Fold into potatoes the egg whites and chopped pecans.
Place in 1 tablespoon buttered casserole or ring.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in 350° oven. Serves 8.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions. Bake three thin layers of cake for stacking.
After cooling, put a layer of cake on cake plate.
Top with a layer of strawberries and a layer of Cool Whip. Repeat until all is used.
Top with a large strawberry.

title: overnight french toast deluxe
directions: Place bread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk, sugar, salt, orange juice and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour mixture over bread slices; turn slices over to coat evenly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: ida flint's english christmas pudding
directions: Use small can of beer to help with the mixing.
Mix ingredients in order given.
Well-grease bowls.
Fill bowls 2/3 full, then cover with wax paper and tinfoil.
Tie down with string.
Water level is 3/4 way up the bowl.
Boil for 5 hours. Keep on low fire.
Keep adding water; do not let dry boil.
After 5 hours, remove pudding from saucepan and uncover them.
Pour rum or brandy over the top slowly.
Re-wrap with clean wax paper and foil; re-tie.
Keep in cool place until needed.
Freezes well.
On the day to be used, boil on low for 2 hours.

title: anise crisps
directions: Beat eggs, sugar,
mayonnaise
and extract with a mixer on medium speed.
Add flour and powder to sugar mixture 1/3 at a time, beating
well
after	each
addition.
Stir
in
nuts. Cover and chill overnight.

title: chow mein noodle candy
directions: Melt morsels in double broiler, then add nuts and noodles. Drop in clumps onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: cheese cake
directions: Put graham crackers in a sack and break into pieces.
Put them in a bowl and pour in melted butter.
Mix well and press into pie pan.
Store in refrigerator while preparing filling.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion.
Saute.
Mix all other ingredients (except tortillas) together.
Heat.
Add meat and onion.
Lay a layer of tortillas in casserole, then alternate with meat mixture. Repeat until all is used up.
Spread grated cheese on top and bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: mom's corn chowder
directions: Fry
fat
back.
Saute onion in fat.
Cube potatoes and cook until
tender (do not completely cover with water).
Add creamed corn,
canned
milk
and enough whole milk to desired thickness. Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot with fat back sprinkled on top.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Add oatmeal to boiling water; let stand 20 minutes.
Cream sugar, margarine and eggs (one at a time).
Add oatmeal.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Place in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: champagne sunsets
directions: Pour 1/2 cup juice into each of 8 champagne glasses.
Add 1/4 cup champagne and top with 1 tablespoon grenadine.
Let stand 2 minutes; garnish with orange rind curls.
Yield:
8 servings (about 111 calories per 3/4 cup serving).

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all together and mix.
Put in the refrigerator overnight.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake (old fashion)
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients three times.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the milk.
Makes 3 layers.

title: peanut butter ball candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Roll into ball.
Chill and dip in melted chocolate.
Chill again.

title: maria's chicken marsala
directions: Mix flour and pepper.
Dredge chicken to coat.
Shake off excess flour.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter and oil in skillet.
Add chicken.
Cook about 8 minutes (4 minutes each side).
Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Add onion and garlic; saute in oil mix. Add mushrooms and garlic; saute in oil mix.
Add mushrooms and cook only abut 3 minutes.
Return chicken to pan; add wine and broth.
Reduce heat and cook until juices thicken.
Add remaining butter.
Serve warm.

title: corn and jalapeno cheese soup
directions: In a 4 to 5-quart pan, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and cumin and cook, stirring often, until onion is soft but not brown.
Smooth blend 1 to 2 tablespoons of the broth with cornstarch.
Pour cornstarch mixture and remaining broth into pan; add corn, pepper and 1/4 cup salsa.
Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring.
Pour into a tureen or 4 wide bowls.
Offer cheese, salsa and corn tortilla chips.

title: frozen lime-mint salad
directions: Measure butter mints as whole pieces first, then finely crush. Combine all ingredients, except Cool Whip.
Put mix in refrigerator for a few hours.
Fold in Cool Whip and spoon into paper muffin cups and freeze.
Serve frozen from freezer.
Can also freeze in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and cut into squares.

title: skillet cornbreads
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Grease 2 cast-iron skillets.
Pour 1/2 mixture into each skillet.
Bake in 400° oven for 50 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes two cornbreads.

title: peggy's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice into skillet (do not use an iron skillet).
Add water and cover.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, then add sugar and oleo.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Cover and cook over moderate heat until tender.
Remove cover and stir until syrup is slightly thick.

title: shower punch
directions: Combine al ingredients and mix well.
Divide in half.
Place each half of punch mixture in gallon jug.
Add 1/2 large can crushed pineapple to each jug.
Add enough water to finish filling jug.
Chill until slush.
Serve and enjoy!

title: egg pastry
directions: Measure flour and salt; cut in shortening.
Mix egg, water and vinegar; add gradually to flour as you stir lightly with fork. Roll out and place in pans.
Should make 3 crusts.
Bake in 475° oven until lightly browned.
For unbaked pies, prick with fork.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Cook cornbread according to package.
Crumble cornbread.
Add 1/2 cup celery, 1 onion (diced) and sage to taste.
Mix well. Debone chicken and add to mix and your soup.
Cook 30 minutes. Ready to serve.

title: tar bars
directions: Mix ingredients together. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine first four ingredients, beat well.
Add eggs and beat again. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Drop small balls of dough on cookie sheet and flatten slightly with fork. Bake in 375° oven for 10-12 min.
Makes lots of cookies, may want to cut recipe in half.

title: preachers' delight
directions: Brown beef in 2 teaspoons butter and drain.
Mix soups, onion, celery and add to beef. Add noodles and put in casserole dish. Sprinkle with noodles. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chilies.
Pour some corn mixture in bottom of greased casserole, then a layer of chilies and cheese.
Alternate layers, ending with cheese.

title: hasty peach cobbler
directions: Heat peaches and butter on stove top until boiling.
Mix flour, sugar, milk, baking powder and salt into batter.
Pour into rectangle baking dish.
Add boiling peaches on top.
Bake in 400° oven 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chinese wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter well.
Add sugar, salt, flour, vanilla and nuts. Drop by 1/2 teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
When cool, shake gently in bag of powdered sugar.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Put into large 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole.
Top with 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: noodle broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in oil for 3 minutes.
Heat broth to boiling and gradually add cooked noodles.
Cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes. Add broccoli and garlic and cook for 4 minutes.
Add milk, cheese and pepper.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Serves 12.

title: edna's brownies
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and mix thoroughly with butter.
Add 2 eggs, one at a time, and beat into mixture.
Add 1/2 cup of flour, 2 tablespoons milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Melt 2 squares baking chocolate and add to mixture.
Lastly, add 1/2 cup walnuts which have been handled with floured hands.
Bake in 8-inch square pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
This recipe is 50 years old.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Mix cream cheese, pudding, powdered sugar and milk all together (hand mixer).
Add Cool Whip.
Grind cookies in food processor. Place 1/2 cookie crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour all filling in middle.
Place rest of crumbs on top.
Put gummy worms on top.
Refrigerate.

title: carrot and cabbage salad
directions: Toss carrots with cabbage and radishes.
Chill.
To make dressing, beat olive oil with vinegar, onion, salt and pepper. Toss salad with dressing.
Garnish with parsley sprigs (optional). Enjoy!

title: t.j. miracle soup
directions: Cut vegetables in medium pieces and boil, covered with water for ten minutes. Then lower heat and simmer until vegetables are soft. Add seasonings if desired.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pie filling.
Drizzle melted butter over top of ingredients.
Sprinkle on nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: In small mixing bowl combine corn syrup with peanut butter. When well mixed, gradually add nonfat dry milk and sifted confectioners sugar.
Shape into a roll about 3/4 inch in diameter.
(Roll in chopped nuts if desired.) Wrap in waxed paper and chill.
Cut into 24 (1-inch) pieces.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour hot milk over bread crumbs; add the rest of ingredients as they come in recipe.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat yolks of 2 eggs.
Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and milk.
Boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue made with 2 egg whites and 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Brown the topping.

title: peach cake
directions: Beat for 3 minutes with electric mixer. Pour into 3 (8-inch) sprayed cake pans. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes or until tests done. Cool.

title: super fudge cupcakes
directions: Use cupcake liners in muffin tins.
Heat oven to 350°.
In a large pan, cook pudding as directed on package.
Stir cake mix into hot pudding.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into each cup.
Sprinkle each with chocolate pieces and nuts.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle powdered sugar on each cupcake while cooling.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.
The best!

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Fry chicken in hot oil until brown.
Do not cook through. Arrange chicken in baking dish.
Saute with margarine, chopped onion, garlic, and chopped cilantro (lightly).
Add salt and pepper.
Add peppers and mushrooms to top of chicken.
Pour tomato sauce and water over top and bake for an hour at 350° (gas 4).

title: peanut butter spread
directions: Combine all ingredients in microwave bowl; blend well. Microwave on High for 1 minute and gently stir to swirl mixture. (Do not overcook; chocolate will soften when stirred.)
Spoon into pretty bowl and serve with graham crackers or vanilla wafers.

title: lip licking potato slices
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Cut into 1/2-inch lengthwise slices.
Do not peel.
Place in single layer on greased baking sheet.
Mix melted butter, onion, salt, and pepper.
Spoon over potatoes.
Cover with foil and bake in a 425° oven for 35-40 minutes, until potatoes are tender when pierced with a fork.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: green chili stew
directions: Boil pork neck bone in 1 quart of water until meat falls from bone.
Cool; remove bone.
Add all other ingredients.
Bring to boil; then cook over low heat until potatoes are done.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Combine the grated Swiss cheese and Vidalia onions with the mayonnaise.
Place in baking dish.
If desired, add a few drops of Tabasco to give it a zip.
Make sure the Tabasco sauce is mixed well with other ingredients.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until lightly browned on top. Serve with crackers.
Vegetable crackers are especially delicious.
Great summertime appetizer.

title: old fashioned potato candy
directions: Boil one large potato until done. Mash until there are no lumps. Add vanilla flavoring. Mix as much sifted powdered sugar as needed until the mixture can be rolled out 1/4 inch thick. Spread dough with smooth peanut butter. Roll like a jelly roll. Chill and slice.

title: flancate(oven baked)
directions: Mix together margarine and flour like you would for pie crust. Then mix together egg yolks, sour cream and vanilla; add to flour mixture and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: divinity frosting
directions: Combine the first three ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until clear, stirring constantly.
Cook, without stirring, until 240° on candy thermometer or until threads.

title: creamy green beans
directions: Cook green beans and onion together over low heat for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Add soup and stir gently.
Mixture should be thick enough for easy serving.
Pour in greased baking dish. About 30 minutes before serving, sprinkle the French fried onions over top. Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until onions are nice and brown and beans bubble.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple breakfast sandwiches
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in small bowl, set aside. Separate biscuits and press into 3-inch circles, place on greased pan.
Sprinkle with cheese, top with apple ring.
Sprinkle the mixture over and put a pat of butter on each one.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: hot crab meat
directions: Pour 1 quart milk in saucepan.
Boil.
Add juice of 1 lemon. Let curds and whey separate.
Pour through strainer.
Eat on crackers.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread in a large bowl.
Heat oil in a pan.
Dip bread in mix and put in pan.
Bake both sides.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix powdered sugar, flour, baking soda and cream of tartar together.
Add margarine, egg, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Roll out on powdered sugar.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in an airtight container.
Use 1/4 cup of mix to 1 cup of hot water.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind peppers, carrots, tomatoes and onions.

Drain well. Add sugar, vinegar, salt and flour. Use a little vinegar to make a paste with the flour. Mix well. Add mustard and celery seed. Cook 15 minutes. Add salad dressing. Pack in jars while hot and seal.

title: no mayo potato salad
directions: While potatoes are still hot, combine mustard, pepper, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, olive oil, vinegar and garlic. Whisk until emulsified; pour over potatoes.
Add scallions and toss all.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grate and drain zucchini good.
Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and stir in drained zucchini, sifted flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add to egg mixture and blend well.
Add nuts. Pour into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Mix well and cool or freeze.
Thaw to a slush; add 1 to 2 liters 7-Up when ready to serve.

title: pickled watermelon rind
directions: Trim skin from firm rind of underripe melon. Cut into 1-inch cubes.
Soak 2 hours in salt water to cover. Drain.
Cover with cold unsalted water.
Bring to
a boil.
Cook until tender, about 10 minutes. Drain.

title: mazetti
directions: Use a wok or large saucepan to heat the oil.
Stir-fry the onion and carrot for 3 minutes.
Add garlic, ginger and red pepper.
Stir-fry for 1/2 minute.
Add green beans, broth, water and soy sauce.
Cover.
Bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes more.
Lower heat to simmer.
Add corn, ham and mushrooms.
Return to a boil, stirring.
Cover.
Turn off heat and let sit for 5 minutes.
Top with Chinese noodles and serve.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper. Drain. Add remaining ingredients (except cheese) and cook until mixed well. Place in a 9 x 13-inch dish and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° until hot and bubbly. Serve with Tostitos.

title: delicious chicken
directions: Place deboned, cooked chicken in an 11 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix soups and milk.
Pour over chicken. Spread stuffing mix over top.
Melt butter with broth and pour over last.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Mix zucchini, onion, rice and seasonings.
Pour tomatoes over this. Add cheese and bacon on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: caramel frosting for angel food cake
directions: Boil in a heavy pan until scorched on bottom and reduced to 1/2 what you started with in pan. Pour over cake.

title: chive buttered carrots
directions: Prepare and cook carrots by steaming or boiling until somewhat tender.

title: rice pudding
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks.
Add sugar, salt, milk, vanilla and rice.
(Add raisins, if desired.)
Stiffly beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Turn into baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken marbella
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the brown sugar and white wine.
Marinate overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange chicken with marinade in a single layer.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and white wine.
Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour, basting frequently.

title: three cheese vegetable lasagna
directions: Saute the first 5 ingredients in nonstick skillet until vegetables are softened.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Mix cheeses.
Spoon half of sauce in bottom of a sprayed 12 x 8-inch casserole dish.
Place 1/2 noodles on top.
Spread with half cheeses; place noodles on top, and top with remaining sauce and cheeses.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: coleslaw - icebox
directions: Boil and pour over cabbage mixture after the 2 hours.
Let stand at least 24 hours in refrigerator.
The longer it stands, the better.
Makes approximately 1 gallon.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl combine cooked macaroni, eggs, celery, onion and chicken.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Prepare chocolate cake mix according to directions.
Pour in pan.
Mix coconut, cream cheese, powdered sugar and butter.
Drop on top of cake batter, small spoonfuls of mixture.
Bake according to package directions.

title: tamale bake
directions: Brown beef
and onions.
Pour off fat.
Add salt, chili powder and
tomatoes.
Cover
and
simmer for 20 minutes.
Add corn and half
of
the olives.
While meat simmers, make corn muffin mix as
directed
on
package.
Put
meat mixture into casserole pan and top with prepared corn muffin mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Sprinkle cheese and remaining olives on top.

title: pie meringue
directions: Blend cold water and cornstarch; add boiling water and cook, stir until clear and thick.
Let stand until cold.
Using mixer on high speed, beat egg whites until foamy, gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Combine the cornstarch mixture and stiff egg whites, mix on low speed, add vanilla and salt.
Beat at high speed until stiff and put on pie.

title: sauteed veal strips
directions: Saute bay leaves in oil for 1 minute.
Add veal strips and cook over high heat for 3 minutes, turning several times.
Add lemon juice, pepper and parsley.
Toss with veal and cook for 3 to 5 minutes more.
Remove bay leaves and serve at once.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in very little salted water; drain. Combine with white sauce, cheese and eggs.
Turn into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs and Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: grandma sheffer's meat loaf
directions: Mix together all except about 1/4 cup crumbs.
Roll into large sausage shape and roll in remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake 1 hour in preheated oven at 350°.
May be served warm but best served sliced as cold meat/deli style on bread of choice.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute vegetables until clear.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cook for 15 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom soup and 1/2 can of water; cook about 20 minutes.
Add crawfish and cook 20 to 25 minutes. Add your favorite seasonings.
Add onion tops and parsley as desired.
Serve over rice.

title: processor blue cheese dressing
directions: Follow directions for making the processor thousand island dressing through the emulsion stage.
Add the sour cream, Blue cheese, parsley and heavy cream.
Pulse just to blend.
Chill. Makes about 2 cups.

title: tater tot casserole(great for pot luck dinners!)
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees. In cake pan, combine potatoes, soup, mushrooms, sour cream, green chile and 1 1/2 C grated cheese. Mix well.

title: church pie
directions: Mix altogether, except coconut.
Pour into two graham cracker crusts.
Put coconut on top and chill.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion in butter until clear; add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over 2 pounds of hamburger or spareribs.

title: lobster with chive butter
directions: Melt butter in heavy small saucepan over low heat.
Place mustard in bowl. Whisk in lemon juice.
Gradually whisk in butter. Add chopped chives.
Season with pepper.

title: easy peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust.
Refrigerate.

title: snowcapped broccoli
directions: Put broccoli in 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with Butter Buds. Beat egg whites and salt to stiff peaks.
Fold in mayo.
Spoon onto broccoli and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Prepare vanilla pudding mix, using 1 1/2 cups milk.
Cool, then fold in 1 cup whipped cream.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Slice layer of bananas over cooled pie crust; then put a layer of pudding mix and alternate.
Put rest of whipped cream on top and brown.

title: zucchini squash pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugars, flour and spices.
Add milk and squash. Bake at 375° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients with sour milk and mix well.
Mix hot water and cocoa and add last.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes in 350° oven. Cool, put together with filling and wrap each in waxed paper.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Add to other ingredients; mix lightly.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cover lightly with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: golden meatball casserole
directions: Mix ground
beef,
bread crumbs, egg and salt together. Make 18 meatballs; brown in oil on all sides.
Drain and add 2 cups water
or more.
Add uncooked rice, carrots, green pepper and onion.
Cover
and	simmer 25 minutes.
Add cheese and let melt.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except broccoli.
Layer broccoli and filling in baking dish and cover with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: breast of chicken saute
directions: Shake breasts in flour, then brown in butter.
Add onions, then wine.
Cook until done (30 to 50 minutes).
Remove chicken to hot plate.
Add mushrooms and soup.
Cook until thickened.
Add grapes.
Add chicken and mix thoroughly.

title: festive frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine condensed milk and lemon juice. Stir well, then add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts. Fold in Cool Whip; stir well. Freeze in a glass baking dish or pour into paper cups placed in muffin tins and freeze; when frozen, remove from muffin tins and store frozen in a plastic container. Serves 10 to 12. Can freeze. Must do ahead.

title: stroganoff
directions: Dice the onions, celery and mushrooms; cook in oil until the onions have no crunchies.
Add the spices to the onion mixture; simmer for 4 minutes.
Cut the meat into strips; fry until it is tender and completely cooked.
Salt and pepper so a good taste situation exists and the meat can be judged well.
Simmer the meat for 2 1/2 minutes with the catsup.
Mix the onion mixture in with the meat; simmer for 23 minutes, covered, with the lowest heat required to just bubble the ingredients.
Lower the heat; fold in the sour cream.

title: helen's pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix baking powder and salt with flour.
Add milk and flour mixture, alternating.
Add lemon and vanilla extracts.
Put in cold oven and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix the sugar into the flour. Add the beer, about 4 ounces at a time.
Pour into 3 well-greased 3 x 6-inch (loaf pans) or 2 larger size loaf pans.
Melt the butter and pour over the bread (butter should cover batter). Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix and cream the butter, sugar and vanilla; stir in flour slowly.
Add salt and nuts.
Roll into balls.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: cheese kuypers
directions: Cover cookie sheet with crescent rolls.
Leave 2 triangles together.
Seal edges together.
Rolls will be wider than sheet. Mix cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, yolk and vanilla.
Spread mixture over rolls.
Flip extra roll dough over mixture.
Can be eaten as is or blueberry or strawberry pie filling can be placed on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Combine mixture with remaining ingredients. Spread in greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: great grandma's cherry frosting
directions: Combine gelatin and water; let stand 5 minutes.
Put over double boiler to melt.
Add cherries, putting in all juice and sugar until melted.
Let cool.
Add whipped cream and vanilla. Use any angel food cake.
Fill cavity and sides.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain well.
Combine macaroni, carrots, onion and green pepper in a large bowl; toss gently, and set aside.

title: herbs of provence
directions: Combine herbs.
Mix well and pack into airtight containers. This recipe makes 3/4 cup of mixed herbs, enough for 3 (2 ounce) gifts.

title: pumpkin raisin cake
directions: Combine sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs, mixing well.
Combine dry ingredients and spices; add to pumpkin mixture.
Beat one minute at medium speed of electric mixer.
Stir in pineapple, raisins, pecans and vanilla.

title: turkey and noodle bake
directions: In a large saucepan, melt margarine.
Add onion and celery. Saute until tender about 5 minutes.
Add noodles, turkey or chicken, milk, mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce and salt; mix well.
Turn into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese. Bake in a preheated oven (400°) until cheese begins to brown about 20 minutes.

title: helen scott's molasses cookies
directions: Blend oil, molasses, sugar and eggs well.
Sift together dry ingredients and combine with oil mixture.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll into walnut-sized and roll in extra granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: chicken potato casserole
directions: Line the bottom of a buttered casserole dish with thinly sliced potatoes and onion. Over the potatoes and onion, spread 1/2 can of each soup and top with the chicken that has been salted and peppered to taste.
Cover with rest of soups.
Dot with oleo and sprinkle with paprika. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
After 40 minutes, cover to finish baking.

title: apple mallow bake
directions: Place apples, raisins and water in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Broil until brown.

title: corn pudding(pennsylvania dutch style)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake in a slow oven for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: savory beef
directions: Brown onions slowly in fat.
Cut meat into serving pieces. Add to onions and brown.
Mix flour and dry seasonings.
Sprinkle over meat; add stock, vinegar and catsup.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar. Add egg yolks, flour, milk and vanilla.
Then add nuts and coconut.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350° in three (9-inch) pans.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, sweet relish and 5 eggs.
Combine pickle juice, salad dressing and mustard.
Add dressing mixture to potatoes and mix well.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Slice remaining egg for garnish.
Sprinkle with paprika for color.

title: sparkling salad
directions: Drain fruit and reserve juice.
Add water to juice to make 1 cup liquid.
Bring to a boil and add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Cool and add Coca-Cola.
Chill until thickened; fold in fruit, cheese and pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: mississippi sin
directions: Slice top of French bread off and hollow out inside.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour inside hollowed out loaf.
Put top back on bread and wrap in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. May be cut into slices or use leftover pieces of bread hollowed out of loaf pan for dipping or use crackers or chips.

title: baked potato skins(james tavern)
directions: In preheated 425° oven, bake potatoes until done, about 1 hour.
Cut each potato in lengthwise quarters. Scoop out all but 1/4 inch of insides of each potato wedge (save to serve later). Heat oil to 375°.
Fry potato wedges for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until brown and crisp.
Drain well.

title: tammy's big game steak
directions: Trim and cut meat to serving sizes; pound to 1/2 inch thick. Dip in combined flour, salt and pepper to coat.
Heat 1 tablespoon margarine/2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Brown steaks, adding oil/margarine as needed.
Place meat in baking pan.
Sprinkle with onion.
Top each steak with 1 teaspoon each of brown sugar and ketchup.
Sprinkle with basil.
Dot with margarine pieces.
Cook stock in drippings 1 minute, stirring well.
Pour over meat.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes; remove foil.
If meat is dry, add a little stock or water.
Bake about 15 minutes longer, until browned on top.

title: peanut butter penoche
directions: Boil sugar and
water
together until the syrup forms a soft ball in water.
Add
peanut
butter
and vanilla and beat until thick.
Pour into a buttered plate and cool.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs in mixing bowl at high speed 5 minutes; add sugar gradually beating constantly.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice; fold in next 6 ingredients.
Spread in greased and floured 10 x 15-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle walnuts over top.
Bake; invert onto towel.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup powdered sugar; roll with towel as for jelly roll.
Cool.

title: squash pickles
directions: Slice squash rather thin; sprinkle with salt and let stand overnight.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in pot of water.
Make sure water covers chicken.
Cook until tender.
Remove chicken and pick meat off bones.
Keep in bowl while making dumplings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream the margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar. Set aside.
Mix pudding and milk together.
Fold in carton of Cool Whip. Add to cream cheese mixture.
Layer with crushed Oreo cookies, ending with cookie crumbs on top. Refrigerate overnight.

title: dijon herb chicken
directions: Saut chicken in butter 10 minutes on each side. Remove chicken; reserve pan drippings. Add next 4 ingredients to pan drippings. Bring to a boil. Stir in chives. Pour over chicken.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: In large saucepan, cook bacon until crisp; remove from pan. To drippings, add potato, celery, onion, salt, pepper, thyme and liquid from clams.
Bring to boil and cook, covered, about 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Combine flour and milk; add to vegetable mixture.

title: margaret's pound cake
directions: Cream butter at room temperature.
Add 1/3 sugar and cup flour, 2 eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add another 1/3 of sugar, cup flour and 2 eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add remaining sugar, flour and eggs.
Beat and add flavors.
Pour mixture into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sprite chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick spray.
Place chicken in bottom of baking pan.
Spoon melted butter over chicken pieces so that each piece receives at least 1 tablespoon.
Squeeze lemon juice over all chicken pieces. Salt and pepper chicken; pour in bottle of Sprite.
Cover with foil and bake 45 minutes or until done.

title: no sugar chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter; add Sweet 'N Low, water and vanilla.
Add beaten egg.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Stir into the mixture.
Add chips and nuts.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.

title: linzer muffins
directions: Combine butter, milk, egg and almond extract.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Add butter mixture to flour mixture.
Pour into 12 greased muffin cups.
Insert 1/2 teaspoon raspberry jam into each muffin.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 5 minutes.
Dust tops with confectioners sugar.

title: peppy seafood sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and chill thoroughly.
Serve with shrimp. Makes 1/2 cup.

title: caramel sticky buns
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Sprinkle brown sugar in bottom of greased pan.
Sprinkle nuts and raisins, if wanted. Shake pudding over sugar.
Pour melted butter, mixed with milk, over top and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place frozen rolls on top of all, leaving room for rolls to rise.
Cover with wax paper; let rise.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes, turn out onto cookie sheet.

title: sicilian salad
directions: In large bowl, combine green peppers, carrots, celery and olives.
Set aside.

title: grandma's salad
directions: Put cherries on crust.
Add layer cream, cherries, then ending in cream.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Cool.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Stir all together.
Let set 12 hours before serving.

title: stained glass windows candy
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine.
Let cool.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Cover 3 sheets of wax paper with coconut. Divide the mixture onto the 3 sheets.
Roll up with the paper, leaving 1-inch of paper at each end.
Refrigerate for 8 hours. Unroll.
Slice and serve.

title: party cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon or roll in small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate top of cookies with 6 to 8 M&M's on top.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: michael's salmon
directions: Dip salmon in egg wash, then roll in flour.
In skillet, cook fish in oil for about 5 minutes on each side.
Do not move around in skillet.
In separate pan, mix remaining ingredients and warm, but do not bring to a boil.
Spoon a small amount of sauce onto serving plate.
Lay cooked salmon in sauce.
Spoon additional sauce over top of fish.
Serve and enjoy.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients,	adding	the eggs one at a time. Pour batter into a Pam sprayed tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°. Cool and glaze.

title: 5-ingredient no-knead whole wheat bread
directions: In large measuring cup, warm water in microwave for 2 1/2 minutes on High; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, warm flour in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes on High; set aside.
Mixing in 1 cup increments of warmed water, dissolve yeast; add to warm flour (do not mix).
Add honey or molasses and salt to flour; do not mix. Add remaining 2 cups warm water to flour; mix all ingredients well until you form a sticky dough; do not knead.
Grease 2 loaf pans with shortening.
(Optional:
After greasing pans, sprinkle bottom and sides of pans with oatmeal, sesame seed, poppy seed or your favorite "sprinkles".)
Spoon and divide dough mixture evenly into both loaf pans.
(Optional:
Sprinkle tops of both loaves with your favorite "sprinkles".)

Set loaves aside out of draft (not in warmed oven); cover with towel and let rise for 20 to 30 minutes or until dough is 1/4-inch below top edge of pan and not over. Preheat oven to 400°; bake for 30 minutes and turn loaves out onto wire racks to cool.
Cover with towel.
Enjoy!

title: surprise cookie bars
directions: Spray a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with Pam; set aside.
Cream together the butter and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and evaporated milk.
Combine dry ingredients and stir in mixture. Fold in raisinets.
Spread in prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Meanwhile, heat butter and milk.
Fold heated mixture into first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, oleo, syrup and salt for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda to syrup bubbles.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake on cookie sheet 1 hour at 250°.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking.
Turn out on waxed paper to cool.
Break up as it cools.

title: rub-a-dubs(open face sandwiches)
directions: Mix together
tuna, eggs, dill pickles and salad dressing. Cut 3 or 4 onion buns in half.
Open and place on cookie sheet. Spoon tuna	salad on buns.	Top with cheese.
Brown in oven at 400°.

title: meringue
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until fluffy.
Add sugar; beat until stiff and glossy.
Add marshmallow cream and vanilla; beat until stiff.
Heap on hot filling.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cole slaw dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients. Stir to dissolve sugar.
Pour over shredded slaw.
Stir before serving.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix milk with Cool Whip.
Then carefully fold in rest of ingredients.
Chill in a 3-quart glass casserole dish for several hours before serving.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: kevin's famous vermont flounder
directions: Grease a medium cookie sheet with margarine.
Lay flounder fillets to cover.
Dice onions and tomatoes and evenly cover fillets on cookie sheet.
Slice mushrooms; cover fillets.
Add wine; cover fillets.
Dice Mozzarella; cover fillets.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top to taste.
Sprinkle bread crumbs.
Broil until the top browns, about 5 to 7 minutes.
Slice like "Sicilian pizza" and serve!

title: clam cheese balls
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Stir in clams, pepper and garlic powder.
Cover; chill about 1 hour.
Shape into ball.
In small bowl combine cheese and parsley.
Roll ball in cheese mixture.
Cover; chill several hours to blend flavors. Garnish as desired.

title: turkey, sausage and potato saute
directions: Cut each unpeeled potato into quarters.
Trim stem ends off of the green beans.
In a 4-quart saucepan over high heat, heat potatoes to boiling and reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes, stir in green beans, adding more hot water to cover beans if necessary.
Cook over high heat to boiling and reduce heat to low and simmer for 5 minutes longer.
Drain.

title: turkey chili
directions: Brown turkey and
onion
in kettle together.
Add pinto beans and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until done.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream shortening, peanut butter, sugars and salt.
Add egg, milk and vanilla, mixing well.
Shape dough into small balls; roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.
Remove sheet from oven; place a Hershey Kiss on top, pressing down very slightly and bake additional 2 to 3 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Boil eggs 12 minutes; drain.
Remove shells.
Bring to a boil water, vinegar, salt and pickling spice.
(Beet juice may be added if color is desired.)
Place eggs in hot sterilized jars.
Cover with boiling vinegar mixture.
Seal at once.

title: mock whipped cream frosting
directions: Heat milk and flour slowly in saucepan.
Stir constantly, making a thick paste with no lumps.
Let cool.
Cream together margarine, shortening and sugar, adding sugar slowly.
Pour cooled paste mixture into the creamed mixture and beat well.
Make sure sugar is dissolved.
Add vanilla.

title: starter food
directions: Combine all ingredients, and use to feed Starter.
Stir into remaining Starter.
Let stand, uncovered, 8 to 12 hours.
Cover with plastic wrap; pierce wrap 4 or 5 times with a sharp knife. Refrigerate 3 to 5 days.
Repeat 3 times.
Use all or discard after 4 feedings.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown ground beef and drain well.
Add rice and tomatoes; stir.
Cook about 25 minutes, until rice is done and most of liquid is absorbed.

title: poinsettia sipper
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a simmer; cover and cook 30 minutes.
Remove cloves and cinnamon sticks from pan with a slotted spoon.
Serve warm or chilled.
(At Christmas, put it in a crock-pot on low to serve warm.)

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix together butter, crackers and poppy seeds. Pour half cracker mix into a 9 x 13 pan. Mix together chicken breasts, soup and sour cream. Pour meat mixture on top of crackers and top with remainder of crackers. Bake for 1 hour at 350°. (Make this into 2 casseroles and freeze one.)

title: cantaloupe ring salad
directions: Do not cut cantaloupe in half.
Set out cream cheese to soften. Peel cantaloupe.
Cut off enough of stem ends to make a generous opening.
Remove seeds, being careful not to puncture sides or base.
Cut off just enough of bottom ends so they will stand upright.
Place in fridge to chill.
Prepare lime jello using the juice from pineapple for part of water on package directions.
When partially set, add drained pineapple.
Return jello to fridge for 1 hour or until consistency of thick jelly, but not set.
Remove cantaloupe from fridge, grate lightly to roughen surface.
Spread outside with softened and whipped cream cheese.
Roll in finely chopped nuts to cover outside surface.
Fill cantaloupe with jello and chill until jello is firm.
Slice to serve and top with fruit salad dressing.

title: churn pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and place whole in clean churn.
Cover with water and salt.
Be sure all cucumbers are covered with the water. Set aside for 10 days or 2 weeks.

title: taco salad
directions: Cut lettuce into large bowl.
Cook hamburger; drain.
Add taco seasoning to hamburger.
When cool, add to bowl of lettuce.
Add Cheddar cheese and crushed Doritos.
Mix all together.
Add bottle of Western dressing right before serving.

title: florida salad
directions: Use equal portions of all ingredients.
Mix; chill overnight.

title: fruit jelly
directions: Soft gelatin in 1 cup of juice.
Heat to a boil the other cup of juice.
Remove from heat.
Add juice with softened gelatin. Add lemon juice, bring to a boil and cook about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool 10 minutes.
Add sweetener.
Makes 2 1/2 pints.
Store in refrigerator.

title: russian dressing
directions: In a screw-top jar combine oil, catsup, sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, paprika, salt and pepper.
Cover and shake well.
Store in the refrigerator up to 2 weeks.
Shake before serving.
Makes 2/3 cup.

title: rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Then put one pat butter into each muffin center.
Heat pan.
Combine ingredients.
Then pour batter into hot butter.
Bake until brown.
Makes six rolls.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Before preparation, ingredients must be dry.
Break lettuce into small pieces and put in large bowl or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer with green peppers, onions, celery and peas (cooked to package directions).
Cover peas with mayonnaise and sprinkle with sugar. Top with shredded cheese and bacon.
Chill 8 to 12 hours.

title: broccoli and olives
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
Parboil 3 minutes.
Saute broccoli and minced garlic in olive oil for approximately 3 minutes.
Toss with halved ripe olives.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: quick deep dish pizza
directions: In an 11 x 13 x 2-inch greased pan, pat the bread dough to fit, coming up the sides of the pan.
Sprinkle the browned ground beef on top.
In a small bowl, combine the tomato paste, spices and just enough water to make the mixture spreadable.
Layer Provolone cheese, pepperoni, Mozzarella cheese and top with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan, stir together flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with a fork until smooth and blended.
Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa. Pour hot tap water over batter and bake for 40 minutes.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes after baking.
Top with favorite flavor of ice cream.
Serves 9.

title: chocolate fondue
directions: Melt chocolate in slow-cooking pot.
Cover and heat on high until chocolate melts.
Stir in cream, sugar, butter and salt; cook on high for 10 minutes until blended.
Add creme de cacao and turn heat to low.
Serve with fondue forks.

title: noodles with creamy meat sauce
directions: Crumble uncooked beef into a large casserole dish.
Combine all soups and pour over beef.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until meat is no longer pink (after about 45 minutes of baking, I open oven and take a spoon and cut up meat into small pieces).
Serve over cooked noodles.
Also, good on creamed potatoes, light bread or cornbread.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms; remove and chop stems.
In pan, cook stems, onion, garlic and butter 3 minutes or until tender.
Simmer 5 minutes; set aside.
In pan, cook pork and drain.
Stir in stem mixture, egg, bread crumbs and basil.
Cool slightly and fill caps.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Sprinkle bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan with granola cereal.
In large mixing bowl, with electric mixer on low speed, beat cream cheese until smooth and creamy.
Beat in Ricotta cheese.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla and beat until blended.
Add pumpkin, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg and beat until smooth.
Pour batter into spring-form pan over cereal.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until center is just starting to set.
Turn off oven and leave cheesecake in oven with door slightly ajar for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs, pineapple and flavoring.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add nuts to flour mixture.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheddar bay biscuits
directions: Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes. Brush with the butter and spices.

title: golden nut crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine nuts and butter in a large bowl.
Add cheese, garlic powder, oregano and celery salt; toss well.
Spread mixture in ungreased sheet pan; bake for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in cereal; let cool.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add 1 tablespoon of flour. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add remaining flour.
Sift flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Add along with nuts and banana pulp alternately.
Pour into well-greased bread loaf pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes good muffins, too.

title: holiday bean dish
directions: Using a strainer bowl, drain green beans, corn and mushrooms. Chop green pepper, onion, and celery.
Combine sour cream and shredded cheese.
Blend with vegetables, put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with crushed cheese Ritz crackers, butter and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: walnut or pecan french toast
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well.
Arrange bread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour egg mixture over bread.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Pour melted butter in jelly roll pan.
Arrange bread.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with xxx sugar.

title: french dressing
directions: Bring sugar and vinegar to a boil; set aside to cool.
After cool, add remaining ingredients.
Shake well before serving.

title: shrimp biscuits
directions: Roll to pancake flatness each of 10 ready to cook biscuits. Spread each with cocktail sauce.
Wrap around 1 frozen cooked jumbo shrimp; pin with a toothpick.
Place in hot oven (350°) for 8 minutes.
Remove and serve.

title: won't last cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: no bake baked beans
directions: Brown and salt hamburger; drain.
Add all ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: carrot pecan cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Set bowl aside.
In blender container, combine salad oil, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Blend for 5 seconds.
Gradually add carrots, blending until just grated.
Pour container contents over flour mixture.
Add nuts.
Mix well.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Cook until just tender.
Drain. While the potatoes cook, dice and fry bacon.
Pour over cooked and drained potatoes (bacon and drippings).
Dice onion and add.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Cook in bacon skillet over low heat and stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Pour over potato, onion and bacon mixture.
Mix gently and serve.
May be kept warm in oven at warm setting.

title: baked tomato halves
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Wash tomatoes, trim and cut in half.
Toss bread crumbs, cheese and butter. Mound crumbs on top of tomato halves.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until bread crumbs are brown and tomatoes are hot.
Serves 4.

title: marbled pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9-inch spring-form pan, with hand, mix graham cracker crumbs, walnuts and butter.
Press onto bottom of pan.
Bake crust 10 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: fried cucumbers are delicious
directions: Slice one medium sized cucumber into very thin slices.
