Dredge in flour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Fry in deep fat until one side is brown.
Turn and brown other side.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken with 2 stalks celery and 1/2 of onion.
Brown; add salt and pepper.
Cook until done, about 1 hour.
Drain and debone chicken; save broth.
Boil spaghetti in in leftover broth. Rinse and drain.
Saute remaining celery and onion.
Add Ro-Tel and soups; heat.
Add chicken and spaghetti and mix well.
Cube cheese and mix in large pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix and prepare with ice cream mixer.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash small whole cucumbers.
Soak in ice water 5 hours. Place fresh dill or dill seed, garlic, and clove in bottom of jar. Pack cold cucumbers in jar.
Put 1/4 tsp alum on top.
Mix solution of vinegar, salt, and water.
Bring to a boil and pour over cucumbers.
Place grape leaf on top of cucumber and seal. Pickles must work.
They won't spoil if you store them in a dark place. They are ready in 8 weeks.

title: pear salad
directions: Arrange pears on lettuce leaves (1 to 3 pears per serving). Put grated cheese on top of pears; 1 to 2 dobs of salad dressing on top of cheese. Sprinkle paprika on top of dressing.

title: marinade recipe for grilled beef
directions: Sprinkle meat with garlic salt (optional) and meat tenderizer; let set for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Heat oil in large skillet; add chopped onion and chicken breasts.
Brown on both sides of chicken.
Mix dressing, jam and onion soup mix together.
Pour over chicken breasts and cook until tender (approximately 20 to 25 minutes).
Serve with steamed rice and broccoli flowerets also steamed.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Store in airtight container.
To make tea, place 3 heaping teaspoonfuls in a mug and add hot water.

title: bloody mary bowl
directions: Mix together; pour and serve.

title: butterscotch crunch
directions: Melt butterscotch in a double boiler over low heat.
Remove from heat and add noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper and allow to cool.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except mayo, sugar and vinegar.
In a small bowl, combine mayo, sugar and vinegar. Mix well until smooth.
Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, chocolate chips and peanut butter; pour over Crispix cereal.
Stir well to coat Crispix.
Then put 2 1/2 cups of powdered sugar in paper bag; add Crispix mix a little at a time and shake until Crispix mix is well coated.
Can store in Ziploc bag.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and pepper.
Drain.
Season to taste with garlic salt.
Break spaghetti into thirds and cook according to package directions.
In crock-pot, on low heat, add meat mixture, soup, tomatoes, cheese cubes and Tabasco sauce. Stir occasionally until all cheese is melted and blended together. Serves 6.

title: john's fruit cake(no fat, no eggs)
directions: Place bran, sugar, fruit, spice and almond extract in bowl; mix.
Pour milk over it and allow to stand 4 to 8 hours.
Stir in flour.
Put into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 350° then check for doneness.
If it browns too quickly, lower heat. Use after 2 days.
Freezes well.

title: potatoes with cheese
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine mashed potatoes with onion.
Place over low heat until cheese and butter are melted.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: kent's favorite cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream butter gradually.
Add the sugars. Next blend in the eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in oats and chips.
Use heaping teaspoon to measure for each cookie. Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes until lightly brown.

title: cool veggie pizza
directions: You can use any of your favorite vegetables.

title: vichyssoise(cold but really good.  do not short change the onion.)
directions: Saute onions (both) in butter until soft.
Add chicken broth and diced potatoes; cook until tender (about 20 minutes).
When cooled, thoroughly chop in blender until smooth.
Add cream and milk; mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Chill thoroughly. Serve topped with chives.

title: 20 minute meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape into 8 oval loaves.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Spoon off excess grease.
Pour sauce over loaves and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 30 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer just until well blended.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bacardi rum cake
directions: *If you wish, you can substitute rum and use rum flavor (1 teaspoon for cake and 1 teaspoon for Glaze.)
tags: Jell-O brand vanilla flavor instant pudding mix

title: garlic salad dressing
directions: In blender, combine all ingredients.
Blend till smooth. Chill.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla at medium speed.
Gradually add flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool cake on rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to cool completely.
Wrap well to store.

title: egg beaters
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator.
This is a no cholesterol egg substitute.
One-fourth cup equals 1 egg in recipes.

title: frosty fruit(for kids)
directions: Blend in blender and serve.

title: bagna culda dip
directions: Drain anchovies and squeeze oil out of them.
Mix with cream cheese.
Add garlic powder to taste preference.
Use to stuff celery.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cream and sharp cheese together.
Add pepper and onions. Roll in foil, then roll in chopped nuts.

title: lazy beef roast with lush gravy
directions: Place roast on foil.
Pepper roast.
Blend together the cream of mushroom soup, cream of celery soup, onion soup mix, Worcestershire sauce and vinegar.
Pour over roast and seal with foil.
Bake about 1/2 hour per pound at 350° to 375°.
Result, instant lush gravy.

title: beef stew in crock-pot
directions: Add beef, peas, carrots, potatoes and golden mushroom soup to crock-pot. Mix well. Cook all day on high. Add Worcestershire and stir (after it's been cooking for 2 to 3 hours).

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients until they stick together. Divide and roll into logs.
Wrap each log in aluminum foil. Refrigerate to chill.
Slice to serve.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish and add rice.
Add Lipton onion soup mix on top of rice.
Mix cream of chicken soup with water and pour over all.
Put tinfoil over top of casserole and bake.

title: 20 minute casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly. Pour into 1-quart dish or pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: cheddar top meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, 1 cup Cheddar cheese, 1/2 cup barbecue sauce and remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Brush 1/4 cup barbecue sauce and top with remaining cheese for last 1/2 baking time.

title: green olivada
directions: Drain and rinse olives well.
Drain again thoroughly.
Place olives, almonds, basil, oregano and thyme in food processor or blender.
Whirl until coarsely chopped, scraping down sides of bowl once or twice.
With motor running, add oil in a thin stream. Whirl until mixture is coarse puree.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Best when made at least 24 hours ahead.
Lasts in refrigerator for weeks.

title: cumin vinaigrette
directions: Combine the vinegar, mustard, cumin, garlic, pepper and salt in a small bowl.
Whisk well. Slowly drizzle in the olive oil, whisking constantly, until smooth.
Makes 1 cup.

title: praline sweet potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done.
Cool slightly and scoop out potato pulp into a bowl.
Beat in eggs, 1/4 cup of brown sugar and 2 tablespoons melted butter.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and press all but 1 cup in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Layer softened ice cream over crushed cookies.
Layer Cool Whip over ice cream.
Sprinkle jar of caramel topping over Cool Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Sprinkle the saved 1 cup of crushed Oreos on top.
Freeze overnight.
Take out a while before serving.

title: pasta chicken salad
directions: Combine dressing, mayonnaise, seasoning, salt and pepper. Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and cool.

title: louise blount's zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add grated, peeled zucchini and mix well. Add sugar, vegetable oil and vanilla; mix until well blended.

title: wild rice and chicken (or turkey) salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package and let cool.
(You can place it in the freezer for one hour.)
Add meat, green pepper and pimiento to rice and toss gently.
Combine mayonnaise, Russian dressing and lemon juice.
Stir wet ingredients into the dry ingredients.
Dash of pepper and salt to taste (optional).
Chill for one hour (overnight is better, allows all the flavors to come out, but may make the mixture too wet.)
Yield: 6 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: raisins squares
directions: Cook raisins, stir once in a while until thick (if too thin, add a little more flour).
Pour into pie crust (use small cookie pan), top with crust, pinch top and bottom crust together at edges.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: norwegian pineapple torte
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well; add well beaten egg yolks, pineapple juice and vanilla.
Add sifted flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread in two layer pans.

title: cheese ball
directions: Grate cheese; let cream cheese soften.
Mix all together. Shape and roll in pecans.

title: apple slaw
directions: Dice apples and toss with lemon juice.
Mix with cabbage. Stir together honey, sour cream, caraway seed, salt and pepper. Toss with apples and cabbage.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Melt caramels with water in double boiler until the sauce is smooth.
Layer apples and caramel sauce in pastry shell. Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon and margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle over apples. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: karo fudge
directions: Grate chocolate and stir into milk.
Add sugar and corn syrup. Cook in skillet and stir in butter.
When chocolate has melted, allow it to cook slowly.
When a soft ball forms in cold water, remove from heat; add vanilla and beat until the shine is off and granulation begins.
Nuts may be added at this time, if desired. Quickly spread in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan and mark off into squares.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Press through cookie press, using star tip, onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 90 cheese straws.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Take crescent rolls and unroll one at a time.
On each crescent place a portion of chicken, chili and cheese, then roll up and place in a 7 x 10-inch baking dish.
Pour the diluted mushroom soup over the top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dinner bread dough(makes nice rolls or bread sticks or two loaves of bread.)
directions: Combine sugar, salt, water and melted shortening in a large bowl.
Add dry yeast and allow to dissolve while beating egg.
Add egg to this mixture.
Stir in flour and mix with hands until mixture is smooth.
Warmth from hands aids mixing and is "friendly" to the yeast.
Allow this to rise until double in bulk. Punch down, form into desired size rolls, bread sticks (in a bread stick pan) or loaves and let rise another hour.
Bake at 400° until golden in well-greased pans.
Between 10 and 20 minutes, depending on whether you make rolls, sticks or loaves. Loaves will sound hollow when tapped when they are done.

title: chicken continental
directions: Brown chicken pieces in 1/4 c. butter.
Stir soup, seasonings and water into pan drippings.
Cook and stir to boiling.
Spread rice in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Pour all but 1/3 cup of the soup mixture over the rice.
Stir to moisten.
Top with chicken and remaining soup.
Bake covered at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: gramma's cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and nuts. Add flour and baking powder.
Put through cookie press. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350° until edges are brown.

title: quick and easy pound cake
directions: Leave margarine and eggs out of refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, add sugar, flour and flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Spray bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Wash rice and place in bottom of pan.
Take whole kernel corn and drain.
Place corn on top of rice.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce and water on top of corn.
Next, add onions and green pepper. Brown ground beef and place on top of vegetables.
Next, add 1 can (small) tomato sauce and 1/4 can water on top of meat.
Cover and let cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage; beat egg with salt, milk and mustard seed; add bread cubes to egg mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Put sausage on top; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 40 to 45 minutes. Make night before.

title: egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs and milk, salt and mustard.
Beat again.
Add bread and stir until bread softens.
Stir in cheese, mushrooms and sausage.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: ninja turtle deluxe
directions: Put turtles in saucepan.
Heat.
Cut hot dogs into bite size pieces.
Put into turtles.
Heat until hot.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Serves 3.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Mix 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
In saucepan put butter, milk and water.
Heat to lukewarm. Add to dry ingredients.
Add eggs and 1 cup flour; mix.
Add flour and knead until bread mixture isn't sticky.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Reserve 4 tablespoons of the drippings.
Cook the onion in the drippings until golden.
Remove onions.
Add flour and milk.
Cook until thickened, about 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in sausage, sauerkraut, parsley, caraway seed, mustard, Accent and pepper.
Chill.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: heath brickle crunch cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Mix margarine, egg and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Stir in flour and Heath Brickle. Drop on pan.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken wings supreme
directions: Chop off boney part of wings and throw away.
Cut other part in half.
Put in pan with all ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Keep basting.
Simmer until thick.
Remove lid. Cook about 15 minutes more.
Put under broiler.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Put in casserole dish.
Melt cheese and 1/2 of margarine.
Mix with broccoli.
Melt other 1/2 of margarine.
Crush crackers and mix together.
Spread over broccoli.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cobbler cover
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then cover your favorite fruit with this batter.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream the eggs, sugar, flour and butter.
Add salt, nutmeg and milk.
Stir in 1 cup coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie crusts (makes 2 pies).
Sprinkle remainder of coconut on top.
(Most will sink down, but some will stay at top and get golden brown.)
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: pink angel salad
directions: Mix all together.
Makes a lot.
Can sprinkle coconut on top.

title: banana cake
directions: Put dry ingredients into a bowl.
Melt margarine.
Separate eggs.
Mix yolks with four bananas and vanilla in blender.
Beat egg whites until firm.
Add banana mixture and margarine to dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: poached fish
directions: Use large frying pan or deep pot.
Put oil in bottom.
Put in onions, celery and mushrooms.
Saute until onions are transparent. Add drained pineapple chunks; stir until lightly browned.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine cukes, onions and green peppers in a bowl.
Add sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed; mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
Wait 24 hours before enjoying.
Pickles will last for about 3 months.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place broccoli on bottom of casserole dish.
Pull chicken apart into long pieces.
Place the chicken down the center of broccoli.
Combine Parmesan cheese, soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and wine.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle more cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: very good sugarless fruit cake
directions: Use saucepan large enough to stir up cake in.

title: tex-mex potato wedges
directions: Cook or microwave potatoes until 3/4 done with peelings on. Cut the potatoes into lengthwise spears and marinate in the remaining ingredients for 1 hour.
Grill over direct heat for 15 minutes, turning often, and basting with the marinade.
Or grill over indirect heat for 25 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: More sugar and vanilla can be added to taste.
Raisins can be added if desired at the end.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: Bring the water to a rapid boil. Add the cauliflower.
Simmer 1/2 to 3/4 hour or until soft.
Mash well with potato masher. Make base with flour and butter.
Brown nicely. Add to soup. Add the Worcestershire sauce and parsley flakes.
Add the Dijon mustard to base, if desired.

title: butter dream cookies
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Blend in almond extract and flour.
Shape dough into balls using 1 tablespoon. Press cherry in center.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly brown on bottom.
Greased cookie sheets.

title: pots de creme
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in food processor.
Blend on high until chocolate pieces are smooth.
Pour into 6 pots de creme or demitasse cups.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with fruit, dollop of whipped cream and/or chocolate shavings.
Serve with petite, elegant cookies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter with vanilla.
Add sugar, creaming well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Beat in chopped pecans, syrup and salt.
Turn into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and arrange pecan halves on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: sad cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add brown sugar and mix well. Add Bisquick and nuts.
Mix until moistened.
Bake in a heavy pan (9 x 12 x 2-inch) or iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes, until done with a toothpick.
This cake will fall in center, but is easy and good.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake as directed on box.
Bake and let cool.
To finish, fold cherries into whipped topping. Spread between layers.
Frost with chocolate frosting. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, food coloring and water.
Mix cocoa with flour and salt.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Pour vinegar over soda.
Stir into batter.
Bake at 325° in 2 (9-inch) cake pans for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine Jell-O and boiling water. Stir until Jell-O is dissolved. Fold in strawberries, bananas and pecans. Pour 1/2 of mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish. Let set in refrigerator half an hour. Spread sour cream over the top evenly. Spoon balance of the Jell-O mixture over the sour cream. Let stand at least 2 hours or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: pie crust
directions: In bowl stir together flour, sugar and salt.
With fork, beat together salad oil and milk mixture into flour mixture to make a soft dough.
Press into 9-inch pie pan or 10-inch shallow oval gratin dish.
Press edges to make side about 1 inch high in gratin dish.
Make sides come to top of pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.

title: riverboat chicken pie
directions: Place chicken pieces, white meat on top, in bottom of a roomy pan.
Add onion, water, salt, pepper and celery.
Bring to a simmer.
Cover and simmer for about 45 minutes or until tender. Lift pieces of chicken from broth.
Strain broth and return it to a clean saucepan.
Bring to a gentle boil until reduced to 2 cups. Remove skin from chicken and cut meat into coarse bits.
Add cut up chicken to reduced broth.
Blend the cream gradually into flour, stirring to make perfectly smooth.
Add to chicken and broth and stir constantly over moderate heat until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat.
Line bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan with pastry dough.
Place chicken mixture on top and cover with crust.
Cut 2 to 3 slits into top.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine in bowl and mix thoroughly.
Serve with chips or pretzels.

title: feeding herman
directions: Mix starter and sugar, potato flakes and water.
Let stand at room temperature 8 to 12 hours or all day . At this point, you use 1 cup to make bread or share it with a friend.
Refrigerate the rest of the mixture 3 to 5 days and make bread anytime by allowing 1 cup to reach room temperature.
You must always keep at least 1 cup of starter and it must be fed at least every 3 to 5 days.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, set broth aside.
Cut up onions, celery, pepper garlic and pimento; cook in margarine until clear (about 20 minutes) in a covered saucepan.
Add tomato sauce, water and mushrooms.
Cook 1 hour at medium heat.
Debone and dice chicken, add to sauce.

title: individual pizza
directions: Slice bread lengthways and place on a cookie sheet, sprayed with butter flavor nonstick spray.
Spread on pizza sauce to cover.
Add mushrooms, onion, pepper and meat.
Top with cheeses. Put in oven and bake at 375° for 10 to 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Contains 4 grams of fat per pizza.

title: my chocolate pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except margarine, in microwave bowl; microwave for 9 or 10 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes. If filling is not thick enough after 10 minutes, add cooking time 1 minute at a time, stirring after each minute. Stir in margarine. Pour into baked pie shell. Cover with meringue and bake in 450° oven 5 minutes or cover with 1/2 cup coconut instead of meringue. Bake 10 or 15 minutes.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix first 5 ingredients together (very well).
Add pecans and mix well.
Shape dough into finger size cookies.
Bake until lightly brown, then roll each cookie in powdered sugar.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together the flour, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Combine the oil and sugar.
Add the eggs; stir.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with the pumpkin.
Makes one 9-inch tube pan or 2 regular loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles until firm and set aside.
Chop all vegetables; add dressing and Salad Supreme.
Marinate overnight.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Place cut up rhubarb into greased 9 x 13 pan. Over the rhubarb sprinkle jello and sugar. Cover this with miniature marshmallows.

title: chocolate pie
directions: In microwave-safe dish, add cream and chocolate.
Microwave on High until chocolate has melted, stirring occasionally.
Beat egg yolks well and add sugar, flour, cornstarch and cream of tartar; mix well.
Add egg mixture to chocolate and heat in microwave on High until thick, stirring frequently.
Let cool and add vanilla and butter.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: mexican stack-ups
directions: Brown meat and onions; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Stir frequently. Layer in baking dish (9 x 13-inch), alternate tortillas with meat sauce.
End with meat sauce on top, about 3 layers.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: mexican rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add salt and pepper to rice.
Combine sour cream and chilies in a small bowl.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Layer rice, sour cream mixture and cheese, in that order, twice, ending with cheese.
Top with crumbs and bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: dilled cheese and salami salad
directions: Cut Swiss cheese in julienne strips.
Cut salami in thin strips.
Cut the cucumber in half lengthwise, then slice thinly. Place cheese, salami and cucumber in a large bowl.
If done ahead, cover and chill.
(Can be prepared ahead 3 to 4 hours.)

title: b~b~q baby back ribs
directions: Mix ingredients in jar.
Cover and shake well to mix. Sprinkle rub liberally over and into ribs.
Prepare smoker for long, slow cooking using hickory (mesquite is also very good). Some people prefer to do back ribs using wood from a fruit tree (apple, pear, etc.).

title: southwestern chicken noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: peaches and cream dessert
directions: Beat for 2 minutes.
Spread over peaches, one inch from edge of pan.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tofu roll a la joan
directions: Roll out dough in 4 1/2 x 8 x 1/8-inch thick pieces after mixing all ingredients together thoroughly in a bowl.
Spread spoonfuls of the tofu mixture over the dough, leaving 1/2-inch edges.
Roll to make your rolls 4 1/2-inches long.
Close ends and use fork to press outer edge into roll to seal.
Deep fry in hot olive oil to golden brown, or brown in hot olive oil.
Drain and bake for 10 to 15 minutes in hot oven. Serve like Chinese egg rolls.

title: sour cream christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Mix all ingredients in order given. Chill dough before rolling.
Roll about 1/8-inch thick and cut in desired shapes.
Sprinkle sugar on top of cookies before baking or can decorate with frosting.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes (do not let them get too brown).

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix ground beef and chopped onions.
Place in bottom of casserole dish and season to taste.
Layer with Tater Tots.
Add soup; cover and bake 50 to 60 minutes at 400°.
Remove from oven and cover with cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: "no bake" cookies
directions: Place sugar, milk, cocoa and margarine on heat and bring to rolling boil. Boil exactly 1 minute. Add 3 cups quick oats, 1/2 cup peanut butter, dash of salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Mix until well blended. Drop by teaspoons on waxed paper. Let cool.

title: creamy fruit 'n nut cheesecake
directions: Combine margarine, crumbs and sugar; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch springform pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over ReaLemon; let stand 1 minute.
Over low heat, stir until gelatin dissolves.
Add to cheese mixture with mincemeat, nuts and rind; mix well.
Fold in whipped cream; pour into prepared pan.
Chill 3 hours or until set. Garnish with sour cream and additional nuts if desired. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Take off heat and put in enough flour to make mixture thick and creamy.
Add milk, salt, pepper and onion salt to taste.
Return to heat and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
In baking dish, put a layer of sliced potatoes, then a layer of sauce.
Dot with butter; repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: chocolate s'more pie
directions: Place candy bars, marshmallows and milk in a medium saucepan and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted; cool. Stir 1 1/2 cups of Cool Whip into the chocolate mixture.
Spread thin layer of warm hot fudge over bottom of pie crust.
Gently spoon marshmallow-chocolate mixture into crust.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and garnish with chocolate syrup.
Chill for 3 hours or until set.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Rub butter into
part of the flour.
Use milk to make a stiff dough
cup).	Shape into dumplings by rolling very thin and cut as desired.
Drop into chicken broth.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes. Do not stir or remove top from boiler until ready to serve.

title: ellas' oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and cream of tartar; gradually add to creamed mixture.
Beat well. Stir in oatmeal and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned, cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet; cool completely on wire rack.

title: one dish meal
directions: Put hamburger, onion, pepper and shortening in skillet and brown.
Set off heat.
Add tomato soup, water, garlic salt, oregano, chili sauce, black pepper and spaghetti.
Put in 350° oven and cook 1 hour.

title: canned tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes by
dipping in boiling water; then plunge into cold water.
The
skin
will
slip
off.
Fill
jars very tight and full; leave
1/2-inch
space.
Add 3 pieces of basil and 1 tablespoon salt
to
each
quart of tomatoes.
Close and process in water
bath according to jar directions.
I usually process 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup and mayo. In separate bowl, combine rice, celery and onion.
Season rice mixture with salt and pepper.
In casserole dish, melt 1/4 stick of butter.
In bottom of dish, put small amount of mushroom sauce, rice, then chicken.
Continue layering process.
Pour remaining mushroom sauce on top. Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top. Bake for 45 minutes at 350° in preheated oven.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix
together
and roll into small balls.
Dip balls in melted chocolate almond bark.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Mix in seasoning mix and taco sauce.
Put in crock-pot.
Cut up cheese and add to crock-pot. Ready when cheese has melted.
Keep in crock-pot on low to keep warm.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pie filling in 9 x 15-inch pan.
Spread cake mix over it. Pour melted oleo over that.
Put chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: banana slices with fruit sauce
directions: Peel and seed, then dice orange.
Core apple but do not peel. Cut into chunks, wash and hull berries.
In blender or food processor, process orange, apple and berries at high speed until liquified.
Serve fruit sauce over sliced bananas.
Make 4 servings, 140 calories each.

title: fluffy frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour until paste over medium heat.
Set aside to cool.

title: battle burger
directions: Put hamburger in heavy skillet.
Add onion and small amount of water.
Cook, keeping loose.
Do not brown.
When pink is gone from meat, add catsup, salt and chili powder.
Simmer until meat is thoroughly cooked and seasonings blended.
Let set for a while. Remove "oil" that comes to top.

title: butter toffee cracker surprise
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Line cookie sheet or a shallow pan with aluminum foil. Place crackers in a single layer on the sheet. Melt butter in saucepan. Add sugar. Mix at full boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat and pour over crackers. Put in preheated oven for 5 minutes. Should be very bubbly. Remove from oven and spread chocolate chips over mixture. They will melt. Spread the chocolate mixture evenly and top with chopped nuts of your choice. Put in freezer to harden. When hard, take out of freezer and break into bite-size pieces.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender in salted water.
Drain carrots. Put all other ingredients together in broiler and bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add carrots.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Serve hot or cold.
They keep well for months in refrigerator.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix melted margarine, flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Put applesauce in baking dish and crumble mixture over top of applesauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Brown meats, onions and green pepper in a heavy skillet. Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese. Simmer for 10 minutes. Pour into a 2-quart buttered casserole or baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.
Top with grated cheese.
Return to oven.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Serve hot with tossed green salad and Mexican corn bread or tortilla chips.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Blend in the fruit cocktail (undrained).
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch sheet pan and sprinkle with the coconut.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Melt the butter and add 3/4 cup sugar and the evaporated milk. Boil 1 minute.
Add the vanilla and 1/2 cup chopped nuts and 1/2 can coconut.
Pour over cake while warm.

title: zucchini supreme
directions: Wash and slice unpeeled zucchini about 1/2-inch thick.
Cook slightly in small amount of salted water, covered.
Saute onions and carrots in butter.
Stir in undiluted chicken soup.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, pumpkin and oleo.
Stir in flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in raisins.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown, 8 to 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet; cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: hamburger tater tots
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle cheese over beef mixture.
Arrange Tater Tots on top. Mix milk and water.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruity fruit pizza
directions: Slice the cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Place on 12-inch pizza pan.
Press together.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven, then cool.
Cream together cream cheese, vanilla and 1/2 cup sugar for the second layer.
Arrange the fruit in ring on the cream cheese mixture in order given.
Mound blueberries in center.
Stir cornstarch, sugar, water, salt, orange juice and lemon juice together.
Bring to boil over medium heat and cook until thick. Cool.
Pour the orange-lemon sauce over the fruit, sealing the edges.
Chill.
Not only pretty, but delicious.

title: oreo peanut dessert (frozen)
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, peanut butter and milk together until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over cookies and freeze.

title: quick and crisp dill pickles
directions: Place small cucumbers in sterilized jars with dill weed and cut up garlic in the bottom of jar.
Bring to boil the water, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a full boil and pour liquid over the cucumbers in the jars.
Seal the jars after adding more dill and garlic.
The more dill and garlic, the better.

title: michelle's suicidal hot wings
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Deep fry wings and set them aside.
In a saucepan, heat the hot sauce, Tabasco sauce, butter, lemon juice, cayenne pepper and salt for about 15 minutes.
Pour the sauce over wings and bake about 30 minutes at 400°.

title: lasagna
directions: Layer as follows:
meat, sauce, noodles (uncooked), cottage cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar; add eggs alternately with flour.
Add vanilla.
Place in large greased and floured tube pan in cold oven.
Turn oven to 300° and bake 1 1/2 hours (sometimes 10 minutes longer).
Cake must be started in cold oven. Let cake set for 5 minutes before inverting pan.
Do not open oven door at any time until cake is done.
